text: Tick-borne relapsing fever is a type of relapsing fever that is characterized by relapsing or recurring episodes of fever. It is caused by Borrelia hermsii, Borrelia parkeri, or Borrelia duttoni. These bacteria are transmitted by soft ticks, specifically Ornithodoros parkeri, and through tick-borne transmission mechanisms. The infection manifests with symptoms such as tachypnea, tachycardia, hepatosplenomegaly, enlargement of lymph nodes, and lymphadenopathy. Additionally, tick-borne relapsing fever is also known by its exact synonyms: Relapsing fever, tick-borne, and soft tick relapsing fever.

text: mechanical lagophthalmos is a type of lagophthalmos.

text: Persistent fetal circulation syndrome is a type of pulmonary hypertension and has several exact synonyms. These include Fetal Circulation, Persistent Fetal Circulation, Persistent Foetal Circulation, Congenital Alveolar Capillary Dysplasia with Misalignment of Pulmonary Veins, Persistent Foetal Circulation Syndrome, and Persistent Pulmonary Hypertension of the Newborn.
Acute sphenoidal sinusitis is a type of sphenoid sinusitis, defined as a sphenoid sinusitis which lasts for less than 4 weeks. It is also exactly synonymous with Sphenoidal sinus -acute.
A corpus luteum cyst is a type of ovarian cyst, defined as an ovarian cyst that arises from the accumulation of fluid in the follicle after an oocyte has been released.

Traumatic glaucoma is a type of glaucoma defined as a glaucoma characterized by elevated intraocular pressure secondary to ocular trauma, which leads to glaucomatous optic nerve atrophy and progressive vision loss. It has symptoms including progressive decreased vision, visual field defects, and decreased peripheral vision. Traumatic glaucoma is caused by ocular trauma that affects aqueous outflow, such as trauma leading to inflammation or deposition of proteins in the trabecular network, changes in the anterior chamber angle, or causing chronic inflammation. Furthermore, traumatic glaucoma has the exact synonym "Glaucoma associated with ocular trauma."
Renal osteodystrophy is a type of kidney disease, which is exactly synonymous with renal rickets.
Dementia is a type of cognitive disorder defined as a cognitive disorder resulting from a loss of brain function affecting memory, thinking, language, judgment, and behavior.
Acquired hyperkeratosis is a type of keratosis and it is exactly synonymous with Keratoderma - acquired, Keratoderma, acquired, and acquired keratoderma.

Tinea unguium is a type of nail disease, dermatophytosis, and something that at least has its location in some part of the nail. It is defined as a dermatophytosis that results in a fungal infection located in the nail. This infection is caused by Ascomycota fungi belonging to a group called dermatophytes, which lead to the separation of the nail plate from the nail bed and thickening of the subungual area. Additionally, white islands may appear on the external nail plates, which gradually coalesce until the entire nail plate is involved. Tinea unguium is also known by several exact synonyms, including Dermatophytic onychia, Dermatophytosis of nail, Onychomycosis due to dermatophyte, and Dermatophytic onychomycosis. Moreover, it is associated with conditions like cellulitis and abscess of various body parts such as the buttock, face, finger, finger and toe, gluteal region, trunk, and upper arm and forearm, which are also considered exact synonyms. Tinea unguium also has a related synonym, cellulitis and abscess.

Eumycotic mycetoma is a type of dermatomycosis characterized by its effect on the skin and subcutaneous tissue. It primarily manifests in various body parts including the foot, trunk, buttocks, eyelids, lacrimal glands, paranasal sinuses, mandible, scalp, neck, perineum, or testes. The condition is marked by symptoms such as sinus discharge and leads to the formation of nodules. Eumycotic mycetoma is also known by several exact synonyms: Madura foot, Maduromycosis, mycotic, Mycotic mycetoma, eumycetoma, and maduromycosis.

Jaccoud's syndrome is a type of autoimmune disease and has an exact synonym, Jaccoud syndrome. It is defined as an autoimmune disease characterized by severe non-erosive arthropathy with ulnar deviation of the 2nd to 5th digits and metacarpophalangeal joint subluxation without evidence of synovitis. This condition may be associated with systemic lupus erythematosus, rheumatic fever, and ligamentous laxity.

Hemangioma of subcutaneous tissue is a type of hemangioma, which also falls under the category of skin benign neoplasm. It is recognized as something that primarily originates from endothelial cells and is identified as a disease located in the superficial fascia. Moreover, this condition is precisely referred to by several synonyms, including Angioma of the Subcutaneous Tissue, Subcutaneous haemangioma, and Subcutaneous hemangioma.

Lown Ganong Levine syndrome is a type of syndrome that is defined as a syndrome involving pre-excitation of the ventricles due to an accessory pathway providing an abnormal electrical communication from the atria to the ventricles. It has exact synonyms including atrial tachyarrhythmia with short PR interval and syndrome of short P-R interval, normal QRS complexes, and supraventricular tachycardias.

text: periventricular leukomalacia is a type of encephalomalacia.

@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:intracranial_arterial_disease rdfs:subClassOf :cerebrovascular_disease .
text: intracranial arterial disease is a type of cerebrovascular disease.
Branch retinal artery occlusion is a type of retinal artery occlusion and has exact synonyms "Arterial retinal branch occlusion" and "Retinal arterial branch occlusion."

Vertebral artery insufficiency is a condition that shares similarities with syndromes and diseases that are located in the vertebral artery; it is defined as an intersection of a syndrome and a disease that affects the vertebral artery. This condition is a type of artery disease, transient cerebral ischemia, and syndrome. Additionally, vertebral artery insufficiency is exactly synonymous with Vertebral Artery Syndrome.

Sneddon syndrome is a type of artery disease characterized by the onset of livedo reticularis in the second decade and the onset of cerebrovascular disease in early adulthood. It has a material basis in compound heterozygous mutation in the CECR1 gene (ADA2) on chromosome 22q11. Sneddon syndrome is also precisely known as Idiopathic livedo reticularis with systemic involvement.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:intracranial_arteriosclerosis rdfs:subClassOf :arteriosclerosis .
text: intracranial arteriosclerosis is a type of arteriosclerosis.
Central retinal artery occlusion, which is a type of retinal artery occlusion, is defined as a retinal artery occlusion characterized by the blockage of blood flow through the central retinal artery.

Moyamoya disease is a type of cerebral arterial disease characterized by the constriction of certain arteries at the base of the brain, which blocks blood flow due to both the constriction and the presence of blood clots. It is also known by the exact synonym, progressive intracranial arterial occlusion. Additionally, Moyamoya disease has an exact match in the Medical Subject Headings (MESH) with the identifier D009072.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:intracranial_vasospasm rdfs:subClassOf :cerebrovascular_disease .
text: intracranial vasospasm is a type of cerebrovascular disease.

Bladder leiomyoma is a type of leiomyoma and a type of bladder benign neoplasm, which is characterized by deriving from smooth muscle cells and is located in the urinary bladder. It is defined as a bladder benign neoplasm that derives from smooth muscle cells. Moreover, bladder leiomyoma is exactly synonymous with leiomyoma of the urinary bladder.

text: bladder squamous papilloma is a type of bladder benign neoplasm.

text: mechanical entropion is a type of entropion.

:cicatricial_entropion rdfs:subClassOf :entropion .
text: cicatricial entropion is a type of entropion.

Paronychia is a type of nail disease defined as a nail disease characterized by an often-tender bacterial or fungal hand infection or foot infection due to either bacteria or fungus (Candida albicans), where the nail and skin meet at the side or the base of a finger or toe nail. The infection can start suddenly (acute paronychia) or gradually (chronic paronychia), with puss usually present, along with gradual thickening and browning discoloration of the nail plate. It is exactly synonymous with Infected nailfold, Onychia and paronychia of finger, Onychia and paronychia of toe, and fungal nail infection. Additionally, paronychia has a related synonym: paronychia inflammation.
Focal segmental glomerulosclerosis is a type of glomerulosclerosis. It has the exact synonyms FGS, FSGS, focal glomerular sclerosis, and focal glomerulosclerosis.
Protein deficiency anemia is a type of deficiency anemia that has exact synonyms including "Anemia due to protein deficiency" and "protein-deficiency anaemia."
Deficiency anemia is a type of anemia and it has an exact synonym: deficiency anemias.
Gonococcal spondylitis is a type of spondylitis and it is a type of condition that is at least transmitted by some form of contact transmission.

Severe pre-eclampsia is a type of pre-eclampsia that is characterized by a range of symptoms and disease features. These include thrombocytopenia, proteinuria, cyanosis, epigastric abdominal pain, oliguria, oligohydramnios, and placental abruption. Furthermore, severe pre-eclampsia is defined as pre-eclampsia that presents with at least one of the following symptoms: an SBP of 160mm HG or higher or DBP of 110mm HG or higher on two occasions at least 6 hours apart, proteinuria more than 5g in a 24-hour collection, pulmonary edema or cyanosis, oliguria, persistent headaches, epigastric pain and/or impaired liver function, thrombocytopenia, oligohydramnios, decreased fetal growth, or placental abruption. Additionally, severe pre-eclampsia is also known by its exact synonyms: Severe pre-eclampsia, with delivery, antepartum severe pre-eclampsia, postpartum severe pre-eclampsia, and severe preeclampsia.
HELLP syndrome is a type of severe pre-eclampsia which is defined as a severe pre-eclampsia characterized by hemolysis, elevated liver enzyme, and low platelet count.

Hordeolum externum is a type of blepharitis and is defined as a blepharitis characterized by an infection of the sebaceous glands of Zeis at the base of the eyelashes, or an infection of the apocrine sweat glands of Moll. It is also exactly synonymous with external stye.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:exophthalmic_ophthalmoplegia rdfs:subClassOf :ophthalmoplegia .
text: exophthalmic ophthalmoplegia is a type of ophthalmoplegia.

Werdnig Hoffmann disease is a type of childhood spinal muscular atrophy, which is a severe form characterized by the onset of muscle weakness from birth to six months of age, the inability to sit unassisted, and has a material basis in a mutation or deletion in the telomeric copy of the SMN gene, known as SMN1, on chromosome 5q13. This disease is also known by several exact synonyms including HMN (Hereditary Motor Neuropathy) Proximal type I, SMA1, Spinal Muscular Atrophy 1, hereditary motor neuropathy proximal type I, infantile muscular atrophy, and progressive muscular atrophy of infancy. Additionally, Werdnig Hoffmann disease manifests symptoms like muscle weakness and its existence starts during childhood onset.
Acute proliferative glomerulonephritis is a type of glomerulonephritis and has the exact synonym "acute glomerulonephritis with lesion of proliferative glomerulonephritis."

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:crescentic_glomerulonephritis rdfs:subClassOf :acute_proliferative_glomerulonephritis .
text: crescentic glomerulonephritis is a type of acute proliferative glomerulonephritis.

Suppurative uveitis is a type of uveitis characterized by inflammation and pus formation in the uvea, which includes the iris, ciliary body, and choroidâ€”pigmented layers of the eye. This condition is usually a result of an infection, often bacterial, particularly following surgery or trauma. It presents with symptoms such as pain, inflammation, bloodshot eyes, blurry vision, and eye redness.

Uveitis is a type of uveal disease and is also a type of condition that at least has the symptom of some inflammation. It is defined as an uveal disease characterized by inflammation of any of the layers of the uvea of the eye, which includes the iris, ciliary body, and choroid.

@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:benign_secondary_hypertension rdfs:subClassOf :secondary_hypertension .
text: benign secondary hypertension is a type of secondary hypertension.

Benign renovascular hypertension is a type of renal hypertension and also a type of benign secondary hypertension. It is defined as a benign secondary hypertension characterized by chronic elevated blood pressure in the arteries supplying blood to the kidneys, with a material basis in renal artery stenosis. Additionally, it is synonymous with a condition that intersects with benign secondary hypertension and a disease that has a location in the kidneys.

Esophageal candidiasis is a type of candidiasis and a type of esophageal disease. It is a condition that at least has the symptom of some bleeding and is a disease located in the esophagus. Esophageal candidiasis is defined as a candidiasis that involves a fungal infection of the esophagus by Candida albicans in immunocompromised people, resulting in lesions, bleeding, painful swallowing, and substernal pain. Furthermore, esophageal candidiasis has several exact synonyms, including Candida Esophagitis, Candidal esophagitis, Candidiasis of the esophagus, esophageal moniliasis, and esophageal thrush.
Fungal esophagitis is a type of esophagitis and also a type of fungal infectious disease. It is characterized by having a material basis in some fungi.
Acute cystitis is a type of cystitis characterized by a sudden onset or severe symptoms.

Scrotum squamous cell carcinoma is a type of squamous cell carcinoma, scrotal carcinoma, and something that at least derives from squamous epithelial cells. It has a definition as a squamous cell carcinoma located in the scrotum and is exactly synonymous with scrotal squamous cell carcinoma.

Scrotum melanoma is a type of melanoma and also a type of scrotum neoplasm. It is a type of condition that at least derives from some melanocyte and has its location in the scrotum. Additionally, scrotum melanoma has an exact synonym, which is melanoma of the scrotum.

Allergic bronchopulmonary aspergillosis is a type of respiratory allergy and a specific form of aspergillosis that results from an allergic reaction to the spores of Aspergillus molds, particularly A. fumigatus. These spores colonize the mucus in the airways, leading to inflammation. This condition is characterized by several symptoms, including wheezing, fever, cough, and other allergic reactions. It primarily affects the respiratory tract. Additionally, allergic bronchopulmonary aspergillosis is precisely referred to as pulmonary aspergillus disease.

Prepuce cancer is the same as something that is both a cancer and a disease located at the prepuce. It is a type of skin cancer. Additionally, prepuce cancer is exactly synonymous with malignant neoplasm of the foreskin and malignant tumor of the foreskin.

Spermatic cord cancer is the same as something that is an intersection of something that is cancer and something that is at least a disease located in the spermatic cord. Additionally, spermatic cord cancer is a type of male reproductive organ cancer. It has exact synonyms such as Spermatic cord Ca, malignant tumor of spermatic cord, and malignant tumor of the Spermatic Cord.

text: megaesophagus is a type of esophageal disease.

Gout is a type of arthritis, which is also exactly known as Articular gout, Gouty arthropathy, and gouty arthritis. It is defined as an arthritis that has its material basis in uric acid crystal deposits located in a joint.

Brain cancer is synonymous with an intersection of something that is cancer and something that, at the very least, is a disease located in the brain. It is classified as a type of central nervous system cancer and a type of brain disease. Brain cancer is defined as a central nervous system cancer characterized by the growth of abnormal cells in the tissues of the brain. It has several exact synonyms, including BT - Brain Tumour, adult brain tumor, adult malignant brain neoplasm, brain neoplasm, brain neoplasm, adult, malignant brain tumour, malignant primary brain neoplasm, malignant primary brain tumor, malignant tumor of the Brain, malignant tumor of the adult brain, neoplasm of brain, primary brain neoplasm, primary brain tumor, primary malignant neoplasm of brain, and tumor of the Brain.

    :has_exact_synonym "Goiter, non-toxic"@en,
        "Goitre, non-toxic"@en,
        "Nodule-thyroid, non tox"@en,
        "Non-toxic goitre"@en,
        "Non-toxic simple goitre"@en .
text: Nontoxic goiter is a type of goiter that is also known by several exact synonyms, including Goiter, non-toxic; Goitre, non-toxic; Nodule-thyroid, non tox; Non-toxic goitre; and Non-toxic simple goitre.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:lingual_goiter rdfs:subClassOf :goiter .
text: lingual goiter is a type of goiter.
Nodular goiter is a type of goiter, which is exactly synonymous with both Goiter, nodular and nodular goitre.

Endemic goiter is a type of nutritional deficiency disease characterized by a noncancerous enlargement of the thyroid gland, which has its material basis in iodine deficiency. It has exact synonyms, including "Iodine-deficiency-related endemic goitre" and "simple goitre."
Substernal goiter is a type of goiter and has exact synonyms including Retrosternal thyroid goiter, Retrosternal thyroid goitre, and substernal goitre.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:nodular_prostate rdfs:subClassOf :prostatic_hypertrophy .
text: nodular prostate is a type of prostatic hypertrophy.
Proliferative diabetic retinopathy is a type of diabetic retinopathy and has the exact synonym PDR.
Background diabetic retinopathy is a type of diabetic retinopathy and it has two exact synonyms: Non proliferative diabetic retinopathy and Non-Proliferative Diabetic Retinopathy.
Right bundle branch block is a type of heart conduction disease and has an exact synonym: Right bundle branch block with left posterior fascicular block.

A hole retinal cyst is a type of degeneration of the macula and posterior pole. It is also precisely known by several synonyms including "Macular cyst or hole," "Macular cyst, hole, or pseudohole of retina," and "Macular pseudohole retinal cyst."
A submucous uterine fibroid is a type of uterine fibroid that is located adjacent to the lining of the uterus. It is also exactly known as a Submucous leiomyoma of the uterus.

Uterine fibroid is a type of uterine benign neoplasm and is defined as a uterine benign neoplasm derived from the smooth muscle layer of the uterus. It has several exact synonyms including Plexiform leiomyoma, UTERUS FIBROMA, leiomyoma of Corpus Uteri, and uterine leiomyoma.
Oculoglandular tularemia is a type of tularemia defined as a tularemia that results in inflammation of the eye and swelling of lymph glands in front of the ear.
Retinal dystrophies primarily involving Bruch's membrane are a type of fundus dystrophy and have the exact synonym "retinal dystrophies primarily involving Bruch membrane."

Haverhill fever, also known exactly as Streptobacillary fever and relatedly known as Streptobacillary rat-bite fever and Streptobacillosis, is a type of primary bacterial infectious disease. Its definition encompasses a disease resulting from infection that has its material basis in Streptobacillus moniliformis. This bacterium can be transmitted through contact with urine or secretions from the mouth, eye, or nose of an infected animal or through the bite of an infected animal, notably rats. The symptoms of Haverhill fever include chills, fever, rash, and joint pain, indicating its transmission method and material basis while underscoring its symptomatology.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:internal_pathological_resorption rdfs:subClassOf :tooth_resorption .
text: internal pathological resorption is a type of tooth resorption.

Lung cancer is identical to something that intersects with both cancer and at least one disease located in the lung. It is a type of respiratory system cancer and also a type of lung disease. Furthermore, lung cancer is defined as a respiratory system cancer that is located in the lung. Additionally, it has a related synonym, which is lung neoplasm.
Tooth resorption is a type of teeth hard tissue disease and it has an exact match with the Medical Subject Headings (MESH) identifier D014091.

Behcet's disease is a type of autoimmune disease affecting the cardiovascular system and is classified as a form of vasculitis. It is characterized by certain phenotypes, including abnormal immunoglobulin levels, and commonly presents symptoms such as inflammation. The disease is defined as a vasculitis characterized by autoimmune-mediated inflammation of the blood vessels throughout the body, leading to ulcerations on the mouth and sometimes the genitals, and is notorious for causing hypopyon uveitis. Behcet's disease is also known by several exact synonyms, including Adamantiades-Behcet disease, Behcet syndrome, Behet's syndrome, and triple symptom complex. Additionally, it has a related synonym, Behcet's syndrome.
Mucocele of the appendix is a type of intestinal disease, and it is also exactly synonymous with Appendiceal Mucocele.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:pneumatosis_cystoides_intestinalis rdfs:subClassOf :intestinal_disease .
text: pneumatosis cystoides intestinalis is a type of intestinal disease.

Bronchus cancer is defined as a type of respiratory system cancer that is also classified as a type of bronchial disease. It is identified as a cancer intersecting with diseases that are located in the bronchus and diseases located in the bronchiole. Specifically, bronchus cancer is defined as a respiratory system cancer located in the bronchus. It is exactly synonymous with both malignant neoplasm of the bronchus and lung, and malignant neoplasm of the bronchus or lung.

Diarrhea is a type of disease affecting the gastrointestinal system, which is described as the condition of having frequent loose or liquid bowel movements. Acute diarrhea is notably a common cause of death in developing countries and ranks as the second most common cause of infant deaths worldwide. The condition's severity often stems from the loss of fluids, leading to severe dehydration, a significant cause of death among sufferers. In addition to water, those affected also lose critical amounts of important salts, electrolytes, and other nutrients. Diarrhea is classified into at least four types: secretory diarrhea, osmotic diarrhea, motility-related diarrhea, and inflammatory diarrhea. It is also referred to by synonyms such as diarrhea of presumed infectious origin and diarrhoea.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:mesenteric_vascular_occlusion rdfs:subClassOf :peripheral_vascular_disease .
text: mesenteric vascular occlusion is a type of peripheral vascular disease.

Diverticulitis of the colon is the same as the intersection of diverticulitis and diseases that are located in the colon. It is a type of colonic disease, diverticulitis, and a type of condition that has inflammation as a symptom. Diverticulitis of the colon is defined as a colonic disease characterized by the formation and inflammation of diverticula within the colon wall. It is also exactly synonymous with colonic diverticular disease.

Typhoid fever is a type of primary bacterial infectious disease that also has an exact synonym, Typhoid. It is defined as a communicable systemic illness with a material basis in Salmonella enterica subsp enterica serovar Typhi. This disease is transmitted by ingestion of food or water contaminated with the feces of an infected person. The symptoms of Typhoid fever include fever, diarrhea, prostration, headache, splenomegaly, liver enlargement, eruption of rose-colored spots, and leukopenia, which is also described as having a low white blood cell count. The disease is vehicle-borne, with ingestion transmission playing a key role in its spread.

Porphyria is a type of inherited metabolic disorder that involves certain enzymes in the heme bio-synthetic pathway, resulting in the overproduction and accumulation of the porphyrins. This condition is also precisely known as Hematoporphyria, Porphyrinopathy, disorder of porphyrin and heme metabolism, and disorder of porphyrin metabolism.

Hereditary coproporphyria is a type of digenic disease, acute porphyria, and something that at least has a material basis in some digenic inheritance. It has the exact synonyms Coproporphyrinogen oxidase deficiency and hereditary coproporphyria porphyria.

Erythropoietic protoporphyria is a type of acute porphyria that is characterized by a deficiency in the enzyme ferrochelatase, leading to abnormally high levels of protoporphyrin in the tissue. It has the exact synonyms EPP and Protoporphyria.

Cutaneous porphyria is a type of porphyria and a type of skin disease, which is the same as something that is both a porphyria and a disease with its location at least in some zone of the skin. Additionally, cutaneous porphyria is exactly synonymous with Erythropoietic porphyria.

Klebsiella pneumonia is a type of bacterial pneumonia, characterized by an infection involving Klebsiella pneumoniae, which is known for causing symptoms such as pleuritic chest pain, hemoptysis, cough, and high fever. This condition notably affects individuals with underlying diseases like alcoholism, diabetes, and chronic lung disease, leading to distinct manifestations including the production of a characteristic sputum resembling red-currant jelly. Additionally, Klebsiella pneumonia is exactly synonymous with "Pneumonia due to Klebsiella pneumoniae" and "Pneumonia due to Klebsiella pneumoniae (disorder)."

Mycoplasma pneumoniae pneumonia is a type of bacterial pneumonia that is specifically caused by the bacterial species Mycoplasma pneumoniae. This condition is characterized by several symptoms including dry cough, headache, chest pain, fever, chills, and pharynx inflammation, and it has its material basis in Mycoplasmoides pneumoniae. Furthermore, Mycoplasma pneumoniae pneumonia is defined as a bacterial pneumonia with symptoms that encompass chest pain, chills, a non-bloody dry cough, excessive sweating, fever, headache, and sore throat. It is also known by several exact synonyms, including Mycoplasma pneumonia, Mycoplasmal pneumonia, Pneumonia due to Eaton's agent, Pneumonia due to Mycoplasma pneumoniae, Pneumonia due to Mycoplasma pneumoniae (disorder), and cold agglutinin positive pneumonia.

Rift Valley Fever is a type of viral infectious disease that has its material basis in the Rift Valley Fever virus and is transmitted by Aedes mosquitoes. This virus affects both domestic animals, including cattle, buffalo, sheep, goats, and camels, and humans. It is characterized by several symptoms, including hematochezia (passing blood in the feces), jaundice, menorrhagia (heavy menstrual bleeding), and hematemesis (vomiting blood). The definition of Rift Valley Fever includes its result in infection and lists additional symptoms such as ecchymoses (caused by bleeding in the skin), bleeding from the nose or gums, and bleeding from venepuncture sites.

Intestinal tuberculosis is a type of gastrointestinal tuberculosis, intestinal disease, and is characterized by being a condition that involves at least some symptoms including bleeding, abdominal pain, nausea, gastrointestinal bleeding, and vomiting. This condition is also recognized as a disease that has its location in the intestine. Furthermore, intestinal tuberculosis is defined as a gastrointestinal tuberculosis that includes diffuse mucosal fold thickening, the formation of ulcers, and fistulae located in the intestine, manifesting symptoms such as abdominal pain, gastrointestinal bleeding, nausea, and vomiting. Additionally, intestinal tuberculosis is exactly synonymous with tuberculosis of the intestine.
Crater-like holes of the optic disc, which has the exact synonym "Crater-like optic disc holes," is a type of visual pathway disease.

Vaginal Mullerian papilloma is a type of vaginal benign neoplasm, which is defined as a vaginal benign neoplasm that presents in childhood and is considered to be of Mullerian origin. It also has an exact synonym, which is vaginal Muellerian papilloma.

Scheuermann's disease is a type of spinal disease, specifically an osteochondrosis, which affects the vertebral column. It is characterized by an abnormal bone growth and curvature located in the thoracic vertebral column. This condition is also known by several exact synonyms, including Juvenile osteochondritis of the spine, Juvenile osteochondrosis of Scheuermann, Juvenile osteochondrosis of the spine, Scheuermann's kyphosis, and Sherman's Disease. Additionally, it has a narrow synonym, Scheuermann disease.
Diphtheritic cystitis is a type of cystitis defined as a condition that involves inflammation and the formation of a dense fibrous false membrane on the mucous membrane of the bladder.
Diphtheritic peritonitis is a type of peritonitis that is defined as a peritonitis involving the inflammation of the peritoneal cavity by Corynebacterium diphtheriae.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:pancreatic_mucinous_ductal_ectasia rdfs:subClassOf :pancreas_disease .
text: pancreatic mucinous ductal ectasia is a type of pancreas disease.

Exocrine pancreatic insufficiency is a type of pancreas disease and is precisely referred to as EPI. It is defined as a pancreas disease characterized by the exocrine pancreas's inability to produce and secrete an adequate amount of digestive enzymes into the small intestine.

Hyperinsulinemic hypoglycemia is a type of hypoglycemia that is characterized by at least having the phenotype of some abnormal blood glucose concentration and is also defined as a disease that features some form of hypoglycemia. It is defined as a carbohydrate metabolic disorder that involves low blood glucose resulting from an excess of insulin. Furthermore, hyperinsulinemic hypoglycemia is exactly synonymous with Islet cell hyperplasia, nesidioblastosis, and persistent hyperinsulinemia hypoglycemia of infancy.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:chronic_follicular_conjunctivitis rdfs:subClassOf :chronic_conjunctivitis .
text: chronic follicular conjunctivitis is a type of chronic conjunctivitis.

Anatomical narrow angle borderline glaucoma is a type of borderline glaucoma which is defined as a borderline glaucoma characterized by an anatomically narrow anterior chamber angle, potentially accompanied by additional clinical features and risk factors that suggest a high likelihood of future development into glaucomatous optic atrophy. These additional features may encompass elevated intraocular pressure, retinal nerve fiber layer abnormalities, abnormal anterior chamber angles, and/or a positive family history for glaucoma, all without any current evidence of optic nerve atrophy.

Diabetic cataract is a type of cataract that is characterized by the loss of lens transparency secondary to hyperglycemia related to diabetes mellitus. It is also exactly synonymous with Cataract - diabetic.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:toxic_optic_neuropathy rdfs:subClassOf :optic_neuritis .
text: toxic optic neuropathy is a type of optic neuritis.
Hypertrophy of tongue papillae is a type of tongue disease and is exactly synonymous with Tongue papillary hypertrophy.

Congenital toxoplasmosis is a type of physical disorder, toxoplasmosis, and it falls under diseases that are transmitted at least by placental transmission and have their basis in abnormalities of prenatal development or birth. It is defined as a toxoplasmosis that involves a reactivated infection of the mother, which is transmitted to the fetus during pregnancy, potentially leading to spontaneous abortion and stillbirth. Additionally, congenital toxoplasmosis has an exact synonym: Toxoplasmosis - congen.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:parasitic_conjunctivitis rdfs:subClassOf :chronic_conjunctivitis .
text: parasitic conjunctivitis is a type of chronic conjunctivitis.

Laryngeal cartilage cancer is identified as an intersection of cancers and diseases that are located in the laryngeal cartilage. It is a specific type of larynx cancer. Furthermore, this condition is precisely known by several exact synonyms, including malignant neoplasm of laryngeal cartilage, malignant neoplasm of laryngeal cartilages, and malignant tumor of laryngeal cartilage.
Pedophilia, which has the exact synonym Paedophilia, is a type of paraphilia disorder.

Ego dystonic sexual orientation is a type of sexual health disorder, which is also characterized by causing some level of anxiety as a symptom. It is defined as a sexual health disorder that involves having a sexual orientation or an attraction that conflicts with one's idealized self-image, leading to anxiety and a desire to either change one's orientation or become more comfortable with it.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:diffuse_interstitial_keratitis rdfs:subClassOf :interstitial_keratitis .
text: diffuse interstitial keratitis is a type of interstitial keratitis.
Senile ectropion, which is a type of ectropion, has the exact synonym "Involutional ectropion."

Chondromalacia patellae is identified as the intersection between chondromalacia and diseases that are located specifically in the patella, indicating that it's a type of chondromalacia and also a type of bone disease. Additionally, it is exactly synonymous with Chondromalacia of patella and also known as the softening of the articular cartilage of the patella.

Ehlers Danlos Syndrome is a type of collagen disease characterized by extremely flexible joints, elastic skin, and excessive bruising due to a heritable defect in collagen synthesis, leading to significant healing difficulties. It exhibits five cardinal signs to some degree across all subtypes: skin fragility, blood vessel fragility, skin hyperelasticity, joint hypermobility, and characteristic subcutaneous nodules. Additionally, Ehlers Danlos Syndrome is exactly synonymous with Cutis Hyperelastica and elastic skin.
A reading disorder is a type of learning disability defined as a difficulty in reading resulting primarily from neurological factors, which can affect any part of the reading process.
Stiff person syndrome is a type of movement disease characterized by progressive rigidity and is of unknown etiology. It has exact synonyms, including Stiff-man syndrome and stiff man syndrome.

Tinea profunda is a specific type of tinea corporis that is characterized by fungal infections located in the skin. This condition has a material basis in Trichophyton mentagrophytes and leads to the formation of subcutaneous abscesses. It is also associated with symptoms such as abscesses. Furthermore, tinea profunda is known by several exact synonyms, including Deep seated dermatophytosis, Granuloma trichophyticum, and Majocchi's granuloma.

Tinea manuum is a type of skin disease, dermatophytosis, and it has symptoms including itching, paresthesia, and skin desquamation. It is characterized as a disease that occurs in the zone of skin. Specifically, tinea manuum is defined as a dermatophytosis that results in a fungal skin infection located in the hand, with a material basis in Ascomycota fungi that belong to a group called dermatophytes. The symptoms of tinea manuum include itching, burning, cracking, and scaling. Furthermore, tinea manuum is exactly synonymous with Dermatophytosis of hand and Tinea manus.

Scrub typhus is a type of typhus that has a material basis in Orientia tsutsugamushi and is transmitted by trombiculid mites, specifically Leptotrombidium deliense, as well as through insect-borne transmission. The infection is characterized by symptoms including fever, headache, muscle pain, cough, maculopapular rash, eschar, splenomegaly, and lymphadenopathy. It is also known by various names, including Japanese river fever, Kedani fever, Scrub mite-borne typhus, Tsutsugamushi, and Tsutsugamushi disease. Additionally, it has related synonyms such as Chigger-borne rickettsiosis, Chigger-borne typhus, Mite-borne rickettsiosis, Mite-borne typhus, Scrub (mite-borne) typhus, Tropical typhus, Tsutsugamushi fever, and Typhus fever due to Rickettsia tsutsugamushi.

Alpha 1 antitrypsin deficiency is a type of plasma protein metabolism disease characterized by defective production of the protease inhibitor alpha 1-antitrypsin (A1AT), resulting in decreased A1AT activity in the blood and lungs, and the deposition of excessive abnormal A1AT protein in liver cells. This condition has a material basis in a loss of function variant located in a gene disease, and is precisely matched to MESH:D019896. It is also exactly synonymous with AAT deficiency.

Fibrodysplasia ossificans progressiva is a type of autosomal dominant, connective tissue disease, which also falls under the category of diseases that at least have a material basis in some autosomal dominant inheritance. It is characterized by the progressive ossification of skeletal muscle, fascia, tendons, and ligaments, a condition that has a material basis in a heterozygous mutation in the ACVR1 gene. Furthermore, fibrodysplasia ossificans progressiva is known by several exact synonyms, including Stone Man Syndrome, myositis ossificans progressiva, progressive myositis ossificans, and progressive ossifying myositis.

Temporal arteritis is a type of autoimmune disease that affects both the central nervous system and the cardiovascular system. It is also recognized as a central nervous system vasculitis and is characterized by having a phenotype of abnormal immunoglobulin levels. Temporal arteritis is defined as a central nervous system vasculitis characterized by inflammation of the lining of arteries, often those in the head. Furthermore, temporal arteritis is exactly synonymous with Horton's disease and giant cell arteritis.

Kawasaki disease is a type of lymphadenitis and is characterized by various symptoms including inflammation, fever, lymph gland swelling, and conjunctival congestion. This disease is also associated with the feature of vasculitis, which involves the inflammation of medium-sized blood vessels located in the body. Kawasaki disease is defined as a lymphadenitis characterized by swelling of cervical lymph nodes in infants and young children and presents symptoms such as fever, congestion of ocular conjunctivae, reddening of lips, reddening of the oral cavity, protuberance of tongue papillae, and edema of extremities. Additionally, Kawasaki disease is known by several exact synonyms, including Kawasaki's disease, MLNS, acute febrile MCLS, acute febrile mucocutaneous lymph node syndrome, and mucocutaneous lymph node syndrome.

Congenital dyserythropoietic anemia is a type of congenital hemolytic anemia and falls under the category of diseases that have their basis in some abnormality of prenatal development or birth. It is defined as a congenital hemolytic anemia characterized by ineffective erythropoiesis, leading to a decrease in the number of red blood cells (RBCs) in the body and a less than normal quantity of hemoglobin in the blood. Additionally, congenital dyserythropoietic anemia is exactly synonymous with congenital dyshaematopoietic anaemia.

Pernicious anemia is a type of nutritional deficiency disease characterized by a decrease in red blood cells due to malabsorption of vitamin B12. This condition is also known by several exact synonyms, including ANEMIA PERNICIOUS, Addison's anaemia, Biermer's anaemia, and pernicious anaemia. It manifests symptoms such as ataxia, paresthesia, pallor, dyspnea, and fatigue, along with features like glossitis and anemia. The basis of pernicious anemia includes atrophic gastritis, autoimmune disorders affecting the production or function of intrinsic factor, and/or genetic factors.

Megaloblastic anemia is a type of macrocytic anemia that is characterized by inhibition of DNA synthesis during red blood cell production. It has several exact synonyms, including Grasbeck-Imerslund syndrome, Imerslund-Grasbeck syndrome, MGA1 Norwegian type, RH-MGA1, megaloblastic anaemia, recessive hereditary megaloblastic anaemia 1, and recessive hereditary megaloblastic anemia 1. Additionally, megaloblastic anemia has a related synonym, IGS.

Gastrointestinal anthrax is defined as an anthrax disease resulting in an infection located in the mucosa of the gastrointestinal tract. It has a material basis in Bacillus anthracis and is transmitted by the ingestion of anthrax-infected meat. This disease is characterized by various symptoms, including lesions, vomiting of blood, severe diarrhea, and loss of appetite. Gastrointestinal anthrax is identified as a type of anthrax disease and also falls under the category of gastrointestinal system diseases. Furthermore, it is specifically associated with the intersection of anthrax diseases and diseases that have their location in the digestive system. The symptoms of gastrointestinal anthrax extend to loss of appetite, severe diarrhea, diarrhea, vomiting, and hematemesis, indicating the range of effects this condition can have on the body.

Labia majora carcinoma is a type of vulva carcinoma and a type of skin cancer, which is also something that at least one disease has a location in the labium majora. It is defined as a vulva carcinoma located in the labia majora. Furthermore, labia majora carcinoma is exactly synonymous with Labia Majora cancer and has a related synonym, carcinoma of labia majora.

Diamond Blackfan anemia is a type of congenital hypoplastic anemia, characterized by low red blood cell counts with decreased erythroid progenitors in the bone marrow. This condition arises due to insufficient levels of red blood cells because of bone marrow dysfunction. Furthermore, Diamond Blackfan anemia is also known exactly as Blackfan-Diamond syndrome and chronic constitutional pure red cell anemia.

Color blindness is a type of blindness defined as a blindness characterized by the inability or decreased ability to see color, or perceive color differences, under normal lighting conditions. It has exact synonyms including BLINDNESS COLOR, Colour blindness, and Colour vision deficiency.
A vaginal glandular tumor, which is a type of vaginal cancer, is defined as a vaginal cancer that has its material basis in glandular tissue.
Pure red cell aplasia is a type of aplastic anemia and it is exactly synonymous with red cell hypoplasia, primary red cell aplasia, and pure red cell aplasia itself.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:angioid_streaks rdfs:subClassOf :retinal_disease .
text: angioid streaks is a type of retinal disease.

Skin sarcoidosis is equivalent to a condition that is an intersection of sarcoidosis and a disease that primarily affects the skin zone. It is identified as a type of sarcoidosis as well as a type of skin disease. Furthermore, skin sarcoidosis is exactly synonymous with Cutaneous sarcoid and cutaneous sarcoidosis.

Neurosarcoidosis is a type of sarcoidosis and also has the exact synonym cerebral sarcoidosis. It is characterized by involvement of the nervous system, which features conditions such as cranial nerve palsy, diffuse meningeal disease, acute polyneuropathy, myelitis, or hypothalamic pituitary axis malformation. These conditions develop from a type IV hypersensitivity reaction with noncaseating granulomas affecting the nervous system. Additionally, neurosarcoidosis is associated with diseases that have features such as polyneuropathy and cranial nerve palsy.

Uveoparotid fever is a type of sarcoidosis characterized by unilateral facial nerve palsy, parotid gland enlargement, anterior uveitis, and low-grade fever. It develops from a type IV hypersensitivity reaction with noncaseating granulomatous infiltration, especially of the parotid glands, which compresses the facial nerve. Uveoparotid fever is also exactly known as Heerfordt's syndrome.

Cardiac sarcoidosis is a type of sarcoidosis and is characterized by a specific condition that includes symptoms such as heart failure. It is defined as a sarcoidosis characterized by conduction abnormalities, arrhythmias, and congestive heart failure, with noncaseating granulomas present on endomyocardial biopsy. This condition develops from a type IV hypersensitivity reaction with noncaseating granulomas infiltrating the myocardial tissue, especially that of the left ventricle.

Pulmonary sarcoidosis, also precisely known as lung sarcoidosis, is a specific type of sarcoidosis and lung disease. It is characterized by noncaseating granulomatous infiltration of the lungs and supporting lymph nodes, bilateral hilar adenopathy, and pulmonary issues. This condition typically exhibits symptoms such as shortness of breath, fatigue, wheezing, chronic cough, lymphadenopathy, and dyspnea. These symptoms arise from a type IV hypersensitivity reaction. Furthermore, it is a disease that specifically affects the lung location.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:hypercalcemic_sarcoidosis rdfs:subClassOf :sarcoidosis .
text: hypercalcemic sarcoidosis is a type of sarcoidosis.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:perforation_of_bile_duct rdfs:subClassOf :biliary_tract_disease .
text: perforation of bile duct is a type of biliary tract disease.

Hepatic encephalopathy is a type of brain disease that is characterized by the loss of brain function, occurrence of confusion, altered level of consciousness, and coma, which results when the liver is unable to remove toxins from the blood. It also has the exact synonym "Portal-systemic encephalopathy."
Alexia is a type of agnosia and is defined as an agnosia that is a loss of the ability to recognize text. Additionally, Alexia has exact synonyms that include Aphemesthaesia and acquired dyslexia.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:neurogenic_bowel rdfs:subClassOf :intestinal_disease .
text: neurogenic bowel is a type of intestinal disease.

Congenital hypoplastic anemia is a type of physical disorder, specifically a form of aplastic anemia, and is considered a disease that arises from some abnormality of prenatal development or birth. It is exactly synonymous with congenital aplastic anaemia, congenital aplastic anemia, and congenital hypoplastic anaemia. Additionally, it has a related synonym, Constitutional aplastic anaemia.
Urethritis is a type of urethral disease and it has exact synonyms: Non-Gonococcal Urethritis and Nongonococcal urethritis.

Bejel, also known exactly as Njovera and Nonvenereal endemic syphilis, is a type of primary bacterial infectious disease. It is characterized by infections located in the mucosa of the mouth, skin, or bone and has its material basis in Treponema pallidum subsp endemicum. The transmission of Bejel occurs through contact or by sharing of domestic utensils, encompassing both contact transmission and vehicle-borne fomite transmission. This disease manifests symptoms such as moist patches in the mouth, lumps in long bones, tissues around the mouth, nose, and roof of the mouth, which destroy tissue leading to deformed bones and disfiguring the face. The disease primarily affects zones of the skin, oral cavity, and bone elements.

Glanders is a primary bacterial infectious disease that also goes by the exact synonyms Farcy pipes and Infection due to Pseudomonas mallei. This disease results in a septicemic infection and is caused by Burkholderia mallei. It is transmitted through contact with tissues or body fluids of infected animals or via mucosal surfaces such as the eyes and nose. Glanders is characterized by several symptoms, including headache, chest pain, fever, muscle tightness, and chills. Additionally, the infection manifests with fever, chills, sweating, muscle aches, chest pain, muscle tightness, headache, mucopurulent nasal discharge, and nodular lesions in the lungs.

Basilar artery occlusion is identified as the intersection of conditions that involve occlusion of a precerebral artery and diseases that have a location in the basilar artery. It is classified as a type of artery disease as well as a type of occlusion precerebral artery.
Corneal argyrosis is a type of corneal disease and has exact synonyms such as Argentous corneal deposits and Argyrosis of cornea.
Posterior corneal pigmentation, which is a type of corneal deposit, has the exact synonym "Posterior corneal pigmentations."

Coccidioidomycosis is a type of primary systemic mycosis and is also exactly synonymous with primary extrapulmonary coccidioidomycosis. It is characterized by having its material basis in Coccidioides immitis and is transmitted by airborne spores. The disease manifests through symptoms such as conjunctivitis, chest pain, and arthritis. Additionally, it results in systemic fungal infection and the formation of skin nodules.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:scleritis rdfs:subClassOf :scleral_disease .
text: scleritis is a type of scleral disease.
Gonococcal bursitis is a type of bursitis and is also a type of condition that is transmitted by some form of contact transmission.

Gonococcal synovitis is a type of synovitis and is a condition that is at least transmitted by some form of contact transmission. It has exact synonyms: Gonococcal synovitis &/or tenosynovitis, Gonococcal synovitis and tenosynovitis, as well as Gonococcal synovitis or tenosynovitis.
Urethral intrinsic sphincter deficiency, which is a type of urethral disease, has the exact synonym Intrinsic (urethral) sphincter deficiency [ISD].

Central pterygium is a type of progressive peripheral pterygium characterized by a progressive fleshy outpouching of conjunctival growth that has grown to involve the visual axis. It exhibits symptoms such as fleshy bumps on the surface of the eye, a sensation of a foreign body in the eye, decreased vision, and astigmatism. This condition is more common among individuals prone to ocular surface injury, particularly those residing in sunny, hot, and dry climates. Central pterygiums progress from pinguecula. Additionally, central pterygium is associated with at least some loss of vision and features astigmatism as a part of its disease manifestation.

Progressive peripheral pterygium is a type of conjunctival pterygium and also a type of condition that at least has the symptom of some loss of vision. It is defined as a conjunctival pterygium characterized by a progressive (as opposed to quiescent) fleshy outpouching of conjunctival growth. This condition has symptoms including fleshy bumps on the surface of the eye, a foreign body sensation, decreased vision, and astigmatism. Progressive peripheral pterygiums are more common in individuals prone to ocular surface injury, such as those living in sunny, hot, and dry climates, and they progress from pinguecula.

Supraglottis cancer is defined as a cancer that intersects with any disease located in the supraglottic part of the larynx. It is a specific type of larynx cancer. This condition is precisely synonymous with various terms including Ca larynx - supraglottis, malignant Supraglottic tumor, malignant neoplasm of extrinsic larynx, malignant neoplasm of supraglottis, malignant tumor of supraglottis, and simply supraglottis.

Balanitis xerotica obliterans is a type of balanitis characterized by white plaques or patches on the genitals. It has the exact synonym Penile Lichen Sclerosus and an exact match with the MESH identifier D052798.

Thanatophoric dysplasia is a type of osteochondrodysplasia, which is defined as an osteochondrodysplasia that results in short arms and legs with excess folds of skin. Additionally, Thanatophoric dysplasia has an exact match with the MESH identifier D013796.
Proteus syndrome is a type of PTEN hamartoma tumor syndrome that is characterized by the overgrowth of bones, skin, and other tissues. It has an exact synonym, Wiedemann's syndrome.

Childhood disintegrative disease is a type of pervasive developmental disorder and is also a condition that begins in childhood. It is defined as a rare condition characterized by a late onset (greater than 3 years of age) of developmental delays in language, social function, and motor skills. This disorder affects children who have had previously normal development but then appear to regress. Furthermore, childhood disintegrative disease is exactly synonymous with Disintegrative psychosis, Heller's syndrome, and Symbiotic psychosis.

Active cochleovestibular Meniere's disease is a type of Meniere's disease. It has several exact synonyms including Cochleovestibular active Mnire's disease, active Meniere's disease, cochleovestibular, and active cochleovestibular Meniere disease.

Active vestibular Meniere's disease is a type of Meniere's disease and it is exactly synonymous with Vestibular active Meniere's disease, active Meniere's disease, vestibular, and active vestibular Meniere disease.

Active cochlear Meniere's disease is a type of Meniere's disease. It has exact synonyms such as Cochlear active Meniere's disease, active Meniere's disease, cochlear, and active cochlear Meniere disease.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:urethral_syndrome rdfs:subClassOf :urethral_disease .
text: urethral syndrome is a type of urethral disease.

Jejunal cancer is the same as something that is both cancer and a disease located in the jejunum. It is a type of small intestine cancer. Moreover, jejunal cancer has exact synonyms, including malignant neoplasm of jejunum and malignant tumor of jejunum.

Benign vaginal carcinosarcoma is a type of vaginal benign neoplasm, which is defined as a vaginal benign neoplasm that has a material basis in both carcinomatous (epithelial tissue) and sarcomatous (connective tissue) components.

Paranasal sinus benign neoplasm is the same as something that is both a benign neoplasm and a disease that has its location in the paranasal sinus. It is a type of respiratory system benign neoplasm and also falls under the category of paranasal sinus disease. Additionally, paranasal sinus benign neoplasm has exact synonyms, including neoplasm of accessory sinus and tumor of accessory sinus.
Hairy tongue is a type of tongue disease and is exactly synonymous with the overgrowth of filiform papillae.

Moebius syndrome is a type of disease that is autosomal dominant and affects the facial nerve. It has a material basis in some autosomal dominant inheritance and at least has the symptom of muscle weakness. It is characterized by congenital, uni- or bilateral, non-progressive facial weakness and limited abduction of the eye(s). Moebius syndrome is also exactly synonymous with Mobius syndrome, Moebius congenital oculofacial paralysis, and Oromandibular-limb hypogenesis spectrum.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:trigonitis rdfs:subClassOf :cystitis .
text: trigonitis is a type of cystitis.

Venous tributary occlusion of the retina, which is a type of retinal vascular occlusion, is also exactly known as Venous tributary (branch) occlusion of the retina and Venous tributary branch occlusion of the retina.

Tuberous sclerosis is a type of autosomal dominant disease and a syndrome characterized by the growth of numerous noncancerous tumors in many parts of the body. It is also known by exact synonyms such as Bourneville's disease, Epiloia, Tuberose sclerosis, Tuberous sclerosis syndrome, and cerebral sclerosis. Moreover, tuberous sclerosis has a material basis in autosomal dominant inheritance and is related to a condition that is an intersection of a loss of function variant and a disease with at least one gene location.

Paranasal sinus disease is the same as the intersection of a disease and something that has at least one disease located in the paranasal sinus. It is a type of nose disease and has the exact synonym "disorder of nasal sinus."

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:neonatal_infective_mastitis rdfs:subClassOf :mastitis .
text: neonatal infective mastitis is a type of mastitis.

Tetanus neonatorum, which has the exact synonym neonatal tetanus, is a type of tetanus characterized by several symptoms and a specific definition. It is a tetanus that manifests in newborn babies when the birth cord stump is contaminated either by being cut with an unclean blade or through the application of substances containing bacteria. This infection leads to a stiff body, muscle spasms, difficulty in breathing, and exhaustion. Additionally, tetanus neonatorum is identified by having symptoms such as some form of exhaustion and breathing problems.

Loiasis is a type of filariasis, skin disease, and eye disease. It intersects as a condition that is located in some zone of the skin and the eye. Additionally, loiasis is associated with at least one symptom, specifically abscesses. Loiasis is defined as a filariasis that involves a parasitic infection of the skin and eyes caused by the nematode Loa loa, transmitted through the bite of a deer fly or mango fly. This disease is characterized by episodic angioedema in the arms and legs, and cyst-like enlargements of the connective tissue around the sheaths of muscle tendons. Dead worms may lead to chronic abscesses, which can result in granulomatous reactions and fibrosis.

Osteopetrosis, which is a type of osteosclerosis, is defined as an osteosclerosis that has its material basis in the lack of bone resorption, resulting in abnormally hard and brittle bones. It is also exactly synonymous with Albers-Schonberg disease and marble bone.

Purulent labyrinthitis is a type of labyrinthitis, defined as a labyrinthitis which is a bacterial infectious disease of the inner ear, often causing deafness and loss of vestibular function. This condition is caused when bacteria spread to the inner ear during the course of severe acute otitis media, purulent meningitis, or an enlarging cholesteatoma. It is exactly synonymous with suppurative labyrinthitis and bacterial labyrinthitis, and is also relatedly known as acute suppurative labyrinthitis.

Cornea squamous cell carcinoma is a type of squamous cell carcinoma, cornea cancer, something that at least derives from squamous epithelial cells, and a disease that is located in the cornea. Additionally, it has the exact synonym Corneal Epidermoid carcinoma.

Hyperparathyroidism is a type of parathyroid gland disease and falls under the category of conditions that exhibit some abnormality of the parathyroid physiology. It is defined as a parathyroid gland disease characterized by an overactivity of the parathyroid glands, which leads to an excess of parathyroid hormone in the body.

Low tension glaucoma, also known as Normal tension glaucoma, is a type of open angle glaucoma and falls under the category of diseases that feature some ocular hypertension. It is defined as an open-angle glaucoma characterized by increased intrinsic resistance to aqueous outflow without known secondary causes, an anatomically narrow anterior chamber angle, or elevated intraocular pressure compared to the average population. This condition is associated with symptoms such as progressive decreased vision and progressive loss of peripheral vision.

Secondary Parkinson disease is a type of neurodegenerative disease. It is also precisely known as Symptomatic parkinsonism, disorder presenting primarily with parkinsonism, and secondary parkinsonism.

Interval angle closure glaucoma is a type of primary angle closure glaucoma that is characterized by acute closure of the anterior chamber angle due to an intrinsic defect, leading to a sudden, inappropriately elevated intraocular pressure. This elevation threatens optic nerve damage and visual field loss but typically resolves spontaneously after several hours, although it may recur. The condition is known by several exact synonyms: Angle-closure glaucoma, subacute; Intermittent angle-closure glaucoma; and Prodromal angle closure glaucoma. It is associated with symptoms such as sudden pain, redness, headache, and blurry vision with haloes around lights, all of which also resolve spontaneously. Additionally, this type of glaucoma exhibits symptoms like bloodshot eyes, headache, and acute pain, and it features ocular hypertension as a disease characteristic. Interval angle closure glaucoma can be triggered by exacerbation of chronic primary angle-closure glaucoma, often due to medications or conditions that dilate the eyes, thereby narrowing the anterior chamber angle and blocking aqueous outflow.

Paranasal sinus lymphoma is a type of cancer that affects the paranasal sinus, and it is also classified as a type of lymphoma. This condition is characterized by having a material basis in some type of lymphocyte. Furthermore, paranasal sinus lymphoma is precisely known by other names, including Lymphoma of Accessory sinus and lymphoma of paranasal sinus.

Angle closure glaucoma, also known by its exact synonyms ACG - Angle-closure Glaucoma, Angle Closure Glaucoma, Closed angle glaucoma, Narrow cleft glaucoma, and primary open-angle glaucoma with narrow angles, is a type of glaucoma. It is characterized by the closure of the anterior chamber angle, leading to blockage of aqueous outflow and subsequent inappropriate elevation in intraocular pressure, which can result in optic nerve damage and visual field loss. The symptoms of angle closure glaucoma include some loss of vision, bloodshot eye, progressive peripheral vision loss, decreased vision, and, in acute cases, pain, redness, and headache. This condition can be caused by anatomically narrow angles, injury to the trabecular meshwork, and injuries to the anterior chamber, such as neovascularization and uveitis. Additionally, angle closure glaucoma features some ocular hypertension as part of its disease manifestation.

Subserous uterine fibroid is a type of uterine fibroid defined as an uterine fibroid located adjacent to the outside of the uterus. It is also exactly synonymous with subserous leiomyoma of the uterus.
Optic disk drusen is a type of optic nerve disease and has exact synonyms including Drusen of optic disc and optic nerve head drusen.

Aspergillosis is an opportunistic mycosis and a type of condition that, at its core, involves material and allergic triggers related to some species of Aspergillus. It is defined as an opportunistic mycosis encompassing a spectrum of diseases affecting humans and animals, caused by members of the genus Aspergillus. These infections can impact various body parts including lungs, brain, kidney, heart, bone, eyes, sinuses, skin, and the gastrointestinal tract, posing serious illnesses especially in individuals with weakened immune systems. Aspergillosis is also precisely referred to as "Infection due to Aspergillus" and has an exact match in the medical subject headings (MESH) database with the identifier D001228.

Neuroaspergillosis is a type of aspergillosis and a type of nervous system disease, which has a material basis in some Aspergillus and is located in the nervous system. It is defined as an aspergillosis that involves a fungal infection of the central nervous system in immunocompromised patients, caused by Aspergillus, presenting as a space-occupying lesion. Neuroaspergillosis has an exact match with MESH:D020953.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:tibial_collateral_ligament_bursitis rdfs:subClassOf :enthesopathy .
text: tibial collateral ligament bursitis is a type of enthesopathy.

Maxillary sinus cancer is the same as the intersection of something that is cancer and something that, at least, is a disease located in the maxillary sinus. It is a type of paranasal sinus cancer. Additionally, maxillary sinus cancer has exact synonyms including malignant neoplasm of antrum and malignant tumor of the maxillary sinus.

Cortical senile cataract is a type of senile cataract, defined as a senile cataract characterized by the opacification of the lens cortex, caused by dehydration of lens fibers, and is related to aging.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:non_renal_secondary_hyperparathyroidism rdfs:subClassOf :hyperparathyroidism .
text: non renal secondary hyperparathyroidism is a type of hyperparathyroidism.

Twin to twin transfusion syndrome is a type of neonatal anemia and has exact synonyms including Fetal blood loss from fetal hemorrhage into co-twin, Fetal hemorrhage into co-twin, Twin to twin transfusion, and Twin-to-twin blood transfer.

Kwashiorkor is a type of protein-energy malnutrition characterized by a severe lack of protein leading to symptoms such as dehydration, anasarca, edema, cough, and swelling. This condition is further defined by severe protein deficiency causing a lack of albumin, which results in decreased oncotic pressure in the vasculature and increased activation of the renin-angiotensin axis and antidiuretic hormone. Additional symptoms include gastrointestinal upset, thin dry skin, and swelling. Kwashiorkor is also known by its exact synonyms: Kwashiokor, Nutritional edema with dyspigmentation of skin and hair, and Nutritional oedema with dyspigmentation of skin and/or hair.

Maxillary sinus benign neoplasm is equivalent to an entity that is both a benign neoplasm and a disease located in the maxillary sinus. It is a subtype of paranasal sinus benign neoplasm. Additionally, maxillary sinus benign neoplasm is exactly synonymous with both neoplasm of maxillary sinus and tumor of maxillofacial sinus.

Cholestasis is a type of bile duct disease characterized by the inability of bile to flow from the liver to the duodenum. It is also precisely known by the terms "Obstruction of bile duct" and "bile occlusion."
Alveolar periostitis is a type of periostitis, which has exact synonyms including Alveolitis of jaw, Dry socket, and Dry tooth socket.

Female infertility of uterine origin is a type of uterine disease characterized by an inability to get pregnant despite having carefully timed, unprotected sex for one year. It is also exactly synonymous with Infertility, female, of uterine origin.
Eclampsia is a type of pre-eclampsia characterized by the presence of seizures. It has exact synonyms including Eclampsia in puerperium, Eclampsia, postpartum, and Postpartum eclampsia.

Vaginal carcinosarcoma is a type of vaginal carcinoma defined as a vaginal carcinoma that has a material basis in connective tissue. It has several exact synonyms, including malignant vaginal mixed epithelial and mesenchymal tumor, vaginal malignant mixed Mullerian tumor, vaginal malignant mixed mesodermal (mullerian) tumor, and vaginal mixed epithelial and mesenchymal tumor.

Frontal sinus cancer is identical to a condition that is both a cancer and a disease located in the frontal sinus. It is a specific type of paranasal sinus cancer. Furthermore, frontal sinus cancer is precisely referred to by several exact synonyms, including malignant neoplasm of frontal sinus, malignant tumor of frontal sinus, and malignant tumor of the Frontal sinus.

Obstructive jaundice is a type of cholestasis characterized by a yellowish pigmentation of the skin and sclera due to high bilirubin levels resulting from biliary tract obstruction. It is exactly synonymous with Cholestatic Jaundice, Cholestatic jaundice syndrome, and Obstructive hyperbilirubinemia.

Biliary atresia is a type of cholestasis and is characterized by the blockage of the ducts that carry bile from the liver to the gallbladder. It is also known by exact synonyms such as Atresia of bile duct, Congenital biliary atresia, and biliary atresia, congenital.

Frontal sinus benign neoplasm is equivalent to an entity that is both a benign neoplasm and a disease with a location in the frontal sinus. It is a subtype of paranasal sinus benign neoplasm. Additionally, frontal sinus benign neoplasm is precisely synonymous with both neoplasm of the frontal sinus and tumor of the frontal sinus.

Extrahepatic cholestasis is a type of cholestasis, defined as a cholestasis resulting from causes located in the bile ducts outside the liver. It is also exactly synonymous with extrahepatic biliary stasis and extrahepatic obstructive biliary disease.

Paranasal sinus sarcoma is a type of cancer specific to the paranasal sinus as well as a type of sarcoma, and it originates from some embryonic cell metazoa. It is defined as a sarcoma and malignant tumor of the nasal sinuses located in the paranasal sinus. Additionally, paranasal sinus sarcoma is exactly synonymous with sarcoma of the accessory sinus.

        "Ostium secundum type atrial septal defect"@en,
        "Persistent ostium secundum"@en,
        "foramen ovale patent"@en .
text: Patent foramen ovale is a type of atrial heart septal defect and has several exact synonyms. These include Atrial septal defect within oval fossa, Defect, Patent or persistent, ostium secundum, Ostium secundum type atrial septal defect, Persistent ostium secundum, and foramen ovale patent.

Campylobacteriosis is a type of bacterial infectious disease and a form of gastroenteritis. It has a material basis in Campylobacter jejuni, indicating that the bacteria are a primary cause. The disease is characterized by a range of symptoms including abdominal cramps, abdominal pain, diarrhea, and fever. Additionally, campylobacteriosis primarily affects the alimentary part of the gastrointestinal system and has a feature of dysentery. It is defined as a primary bacterial infectious disease resulting in an infection located in the intestine, caused by Campylobacter jejuni. The disease can be transmitted by ingesting contaminated food or water, or through contact with infected individuals or animals. The infection manifests with symptoms such as diarrhea or dysentery, abdominal cramps and pain, and fever.

@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:photokeratitis rdfs:subClassOf :keratitis .
text: photokeratitis is a type of keratitis.
Favism is a type of glucosephosphate dehydrogenase deficiency characterized by a hemolytic reaction to the consumption of broad beans.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:dentine_erosion rdfs:subClassOf :tooth_erosion .
text: dentine erosion is a type of tooth erosion.

Ethmoid sinus cancer is identical to a condition that is both a cancer and a disease, specifically located in the ethmoid sinus. It is a form of paranasal sinus cancer. Furthermore, ethmoid sinus cancer is precisely known by several synonyms, including malignant neoplasm of ethmoidal sinus, malignant tumor of ethmoid sinus, and malignant tumor of ethmoidal sinus.

Fanconi anemia is a type of congenital hypoplastic anemia characterized by progressive pancytopenia with bone marrow failure, variable congenital malformations, and a predisposition to develop hematological or solid tumors. This condition is the result of a genetic defect in a cluster of proteins responsible for DNA repair. Fanconi anemia is also known by several exact synonyms, including Fanconi anaemia, Fanconi pancytopenia, Fanconi panmyelopathy, Fanconi's anaemia, and Fanconi's anemia.

An ethmoidal sinus benign neoplasm is the same as something that is both a benign neoplasm and a disease that has a location in the ethmoid sinus. It is a specific type of paranasal sinus benign neoplasm. Additionally, "neoplasm of ethmoidal sinus" and "tumor of ethmoidal sinus" are exact synonyms for an ethmoidal sinus benign neoplasm.

Exfoliation syndrome is a type of phacogenic glaucoma, iris disease, and is associated with diseases that manifest in the iris, optic atrophy, and ocular hypertension. It is defined as a phacogenic glaucoma characterized by open-angle glaucoma due to the deposition of extracellular fibrillar material in anterior segment structures, leading to blocked aqueous fluid outflow, increased intraocular pressure, and eventually optic nerve atrophy and visual field loss. This syndrome, caused by age-related deposition of fibrillar material in anterior segment structures, presents symptoms such as progressive decreased vision, especially in the peripheral vision. Exfoliation syndrome is also known by its exact synonyms, Pseudoexfoliation glaucoma and Pseudoexfoliation syndrome, and is identified with the exact match MESH:D017889.

:polyneuropathy_in_collagen_vascular_disease rdfs:subClassOf :polyneuropathy .
text: polyneuropathy in collagen vascular disease is a type of polyneuropathy.

:eversion_of_lacrimal_punctum rdfs:subClassOf :lacrimal_apparatus_disease .
text: eversion of lacrimal punctum is a type of lacrimal apparatus disease.

fragment:

:stenosis_of_lacrimal_punctum rdfs:subClassOf :lacrimal_apparatus_disease .
text: stenosis of lacrimal punctum is a type of lacrimal apparatus disease.
Stenosis of the lacrimal passage, which has the exact synonym "Stenosis of lacrimal canaliculi," is a type of lacrimal apparatus disease.

Acquired tear duct stenosis is a type of lacrimal apparatus disease and is exactly synonymous with Stenosis of nasolacrimal duct, acquired, Tear duct - acquired stenosis, acquired nasolacrimal duct stenosis, and acquired stenosis of nasolacrimal duct.
