:infective_urethral_stricture rdfs:subClassOf :urethral_stricture .
text: infective urethral stricture is a type of urethral stricture.
Ulcer of anus and rectum, which has the exact synonym anal and rectal ulcer, is a type of rectal disease.
Post vaccinal encephalitis is a type of encephalitis and is exactly synonymous with Encephalitis following immunization procedures and Postvaccinal encephalomyelitis.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:posterior_scleritis rdfs:subClassOf :scleritis .
text: posterior scleritis is a type of scleritis.

Sapho syndrome is a type of syndrome characterized by synovitis, acne, pustulosis, hyperostosis, and osteitis. It is also exactly synonymous with Synovitis, acne, pustulosis palmaris, hyperostosis, osteomyelitis syndrome.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:chronic_duodenal_ileus rdfs:subClassOf :duodenal_obstruction .
text: chronic duodenal ileus is a type of duodenal obstruction.

Prostate calculus is a type of prostate disease and also falls under the category of lower urinary tract calculus. It is specifically something that at least one disease has located in the prostate gland. Additionally, prostate calculus is exactly synonymous with Prostatic lithiasis, Prostatic stone, Stone of prostate, and calculus of prostate.

Acute gonococcal cystitis is a type of acute cystitis and is defined as an acute cystitis that is caused by gonorrhea. It has exact synonyms, which include Gonococcal cystitis and acute gonorrhea of the bladder.

A dermoid cyst of the skin is a specific type of dermoid cyst that also falls under the category of a skin benign neoplasm. It is defined as a dermoid cyst located in the skin and is recognized as a condition that occurs in a certain zone of the skin. Additionally, it is exactly synonymous with the term "skin Dermoid."

Vaginal squamous papilloma is a type of vaginal benign neoplasm characterized by the presence of a fibrovascular stalk lined by normal squamous epithelium. It is also exactly synonymous with squamous papilloma of the vagina.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:premature_ejaculation rdfs:subClassOf :psychosexual_disorder .
text: premature ejaculation is a type of psychosexual disorder.

Uterine corpus adenomatoid tumor is a type of uterine benign neoplasm, adenoma, and is associated with squamous epithelial cells, mesothelium, and glands. It is defined as a uterine benign neoplasm characterized by the formation of gland-like structures, arises from the uterine serosa and myometrium, and has its material basis in the mesothelium. Additionally, uterine corpus adenomatoid tumor is exactly synonymous with uterine corpus adenomatoid tumour, uterine corpus localized epithelial Mesothelioma, and uterine corpus localised epithelial Mesothelioma.

Dental fluorosis is a type of tooth disease that is characterized by enamel discoloration resulting from excess fluoride ingestion during tooth formation. It has exact synonyms which include Intrinsic enamel discoloration of fluorosis, Mottled teeth, and Mottling of enamel.

Anodontia is a type of tooth disease characterized by the complete absence of permanent teeth. It is precisely defined as a tooth disease marked by the absence of all permanent teeth. This condition is also exactly known as the complete absence of teeth, developmental absence of tooth, and total anodontia of permanent and deciduous teeth. Furthermore, Anodontia has an exact match with the MESH identifier D000848.

Mature cataract is a type of senile cataract, and it is defined as a senile cataract characterized by full white or brunescent opacification of the lens of the eye such that the red reflex is obscured. This condition represents a later stage of senile cataracts and is caused by a multifactorial etiology related to aging. Additionally, mature cataract is exactly synonymous with both "Total or mature cataract" and "Total, mature senile cataract."

Neuroschistosomiasis is a type of schistosomiasis, which is characterized by being a disease that affects both the brain and the spinal cord. Specifically, it is recognized for its involvement in parasitic infections of the brain and spinal cord by Schistosoma haematobium, Schistosoma mansoni, or Schistosoma japonicum. This condition leads to acute or subacute myelopathy, focal central nervous system impairment, seizures, and increased intracranial pressure. Additionally, neuroschistosomiasis is associated with diseases located in the brain and spinal cord, emphasizing its impact on these critical areas of the central nervous system.

Scurvy is a type of nutritional deficiency disease characterized by a deficiency in vitamin C (ascorbic acid). It exhibits several symptoms, including weakness, anemia, petechiae, fatigue, poor wound healing, and corkscrew hair.
Beriberi is a type of thiamine deficiency disease that is characterized by being severe and chronic. It has an exact match in the Medical Subject Headings (MESH) with the identifier D001602.

Endometrial stromal nodule is a type of uterine benign neoplasm, which is defined as a uterine benign neoplasm that has a material basis in cells reminiscent of proliferative phase endometrial stroma.

Malignant renovascular hypertension is the same as something that is both a type of malignant secondary hypertension and a disease that at least has its location in the kidney. Additionally, malignant renovascular hypertension is a type of renal hypertension as well as a type of malignant secondary hypertension.

@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:malignant_secondary_hypertension rdfs:subClassOf :secondary_hypertension .
text: malignant secondary hypertension is a type of secondary hypertension.

@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:panophthalmitis rdfs:subClassOf :purulent_endophthalmitis .
text: panophthalmitis is a type of purulent endophthalmitis.

Uterine inflammatory disease is a type of uterine disease that is characterized by inflammation. It falls under the category of conditions that have at least some inflammation as a symptom. Additionally, uterine inflammatory disease is exactly synonymous with the term "Inflammatory disease of the uterus."
Hepatic infarction is a type of hepatic vascular disease and is exactly synonymous with infarct of liver.
Nutmeg liver, which is a type of hepatic vascular disease, has the exact synonym chronic passive congestion of liver.

Neurofibroma of the spinal cord is the same as something that intersects with neurofibroma and a disease that has at least one location in the spinal cord. It is a type of spinal cancer as well as a type of neurofibroma.

Spinal cord lipoma is a type of spinal cord disease and is also classified as a type of central nervous system lipoma. It is characterized by abnormal fat accumulation in and around the spinal cord, deriving from adipocytes. This condition occurs when at least some disease is located in the spinal cord. Additionally, spinal cord lipoma is exactly synonymous with the term Lipoma of spinal cord.
Neonatal urinary tract infectious disease is a type of urinary system disease and has the exact synonym "urinary tract infection of newborn."

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:epiphora_due_to_insufficient_drainage rdfs:subClassOf :excessive_tearing .
text: epiphora due to insufficient drainage is a type of excessive tearing.
Excessive tearing is a type of lacrimal apparatus disease and has exact synonyms including Epiphora, Excessive tear production, and Watering eye.

Pthirus pubis infestation is a type of lice infestation and also a type of infestation that is transmitted by some form of contact transmission. It is defined as a lice infestation that involves parasitic infestation by pubic lice, Pthirus pubis, which are found in the pubic hair and, less commonly, in eyebrows, eyelashes, beard, mustache, armpit, perianal area, groin, trunk, and scalp. The symptoms include itching in the pubic and groin area, and intense itching can lead to scratching, which may cause sores and secondary bacterial infection of the skin. Pthirus pubis infestation is also known by several exact synonyms, including Infestation by Phthirus pubis, Pediculosis Pubis, Pediculus pubis, Phthiriasis pubis, Phthirus pubis, Phthirus/pediculus pubis - pubic lice - crabs, and simply as crabs.

Clonorchiasis, also known as Oriental liver fluke disease, is categorized as a type of liver disease and a parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease. It is fundamentally caused by the parasite Clonorchis sinensis and is characterized by symptoms such as abdominal pain, nausea, and diarrhea. The disease primarily affects the liver and can lead to conditions such as cholangitis. Clonorchiasis involves a parasitic infection of the bile ducts of the liver, and in cases of prolonged infections, it may result in complications like cholelithiasis, pancreatitis, and cholangiocarcinoma.

Opisthorchiasis is recognized as a type of disease affecting the gallbladder, pancreas, and liver, and it belongs to the broader category of parasitic helminthiasis infectious diseases. This condition is characterized by its association with the liver, pancreas, and gallbladder, indicating a specific intersection in its pathology. The disease is caused by the parasitic entities Opisthorchis viverrini or Opisthorchis felineus. Symptoms associated with opisthorchiasis include dyspepsia, abdominal pain, hepatomegaly, left upper quadrant abdominal rigidity, diarrhea, and constipation. Furthermore, it features conditions such as cholecystitis and cholangitis. Opisthorchiasis is also known by its exact synonym, "Infection by Opisthorchis," and is defined as a parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease involving parasitic infection of the liver, pancreas, and gall bladder, leading to symptoms like dyspepsia, abdominal pain, diarrhea, constipation, hepatomegaly, cholangitis, cholecystitis, and potentially cholangiocarcinoma.

Addison's disease is a type of adrenal cortical hypofunction characterized by insufficient steroid hormone production by the adrenal glands. It is also precisely known as Addison disease, Addison disease, chronic adrenal insufficiency, HYPOADRENOCORTICISM, FAMILIAL, primary adrenocortical insufficiency, and primary hypoadrenalism.

Plantar wart is a type of viral infectious disease, something that at least has a material basis in some human papillomavirus types, and something that at least has the symptom of skin lesions. It is defined as a viral infectious disease that results in benign epithelial tumors located in the skin of the sole or toes of the foot, with a material basis in human papillomavirus (types 1, 2, 4, or 63), and has symptoms of lesions that appear on the sole of the foot. Additionally, plantar wart has the exact synonym Verruca plantaris.

Epidermodysplasia verruciformis is a disease that functions as a type of autosomal recessive disease, a type of primary immunodeficiency disease, and it is characterized by having at least a material basis in some autosomal recessive inheritance. It is defined as a primary immunodeficiency disease that leads to skin squamous cell carcinoma located in the skin, associated with a high risk of carcinoma. The disease is further characterized by an abnormal susceptibility to human papillomaviruses of the skin and manifests with lesions on the body. Additionally, Epidermodysplasia verruciformis has an exact match with the Medical Subject Headings (MESH) identifier D004819.

Chancroid is a type of primary bacterial infectious disease that also qualifies as a skin disease. It is characterized by having at least a material basis in some Haemophilus ducreyi and is transmitted by some form of contact transmission, specifically sexual contact. This disease primarily affects the zone of skin, particularly the skin of the genitals. Chancroid is defined as a sexually transmitted infection that results in painful and soft ulcers, and it is caused by the bacterium Haemophilus ducreyi. Additionally, chancroid is exactly synonymous with Ulcus molle.
Hypermobility syndrome, which is a type of arthropathy, has the exact synonym benign joint hypermobility.
Localized anterior staphyloma is a type of scleral staphyloma. It is also exactly synonymous with Anterior staphyloma, localized, Anterior staphyloma, localised, and localized anterior staphyloma.

:equatorial_staphyloma rdfs:subClassOf :scleral_staphyloma .
text: equatorial staphyloma is a type of scleral staphyloma.
