:staphyloma_posticum rdfs:subClassOf :scleral_staphyloma .
text: staphyloma posticum is a type of scleral staphyloma.
Acute tympanitis, which has the exact synonym acute myringitis, is a type of tympanic membrane disease.

Myringitis bullosa hemorrhagica is a type of tympanic membrane disease and is defined as a tympanic membrane disease characterized by blisters on the eardrum resulting from infection. It is also exactly synonymous with Bullous myringitis.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:anterior_scleritis rdfs:subClassOf :scleritis .
text: anterior scleritis is a type of scleritis.

Female breast central part cancer is a type of female breast cancer, which is defined as a female breast cancer located in the center of the breast. It is also exactly synonymous with malignant neoplasm of the central part of the female breast and malignant neoplasm of the central portion of the female breast.
Vaginal squamous tumor, a type of vaginal cancer, is defined as a vaginal cancer that has its material basis in squamous tissue.

Endometrial cancer, also known with exact synonyms such as endometrial Ca, endometrial neoplasm, malignant endometrial neoplasm, malignant neoplasm of endometrium, neoplasm of endometrium, primary malignant neoplasm of endometrium, and tumor of endometrium, is defined as a uterine cancer that is located in tissues lining the uterus. This type of cancer is the same as something that is both a cancer and a disease, with at least one instance having its location in the endometrium. Furthermore, endometrial cancer is a type of endometriosis as well as a type of uterine cancer.

Inclusion conjunctivitis, also known as Chlamydial conjunctivitis, Inclusion blennorrhoea, Adult inclusion conjunctivitis, or Inclusion blenorrhea, and relatedly referred to as Paratrachoma, is a type of conjunctival disease that is a commensal bacterial infectious disease. It is characterized by inflammation located in the conjunctiva of the eye. This disease has its material basis in Chlamydia trachomatis, which is transmitted by sexual contact. The infection results in symptoms such as swollen conjunctiva and eyelids, along with the discharge of pus and mucus. Furthermore, Inclusion conjunctivitis is associated with conjunctival swelling as a symptom, has its location in the conjunctiva, and is transmitted through contact transmission.

Pharyngoconjunctival fever is a type of viral infectious disease that has a material basis in either Human adenovirus 7 or Human adenovirus B3. It is transmitted through droplet spread transmission and vehicle-borne fomite transmission. The symptoms of this disease include headache, enlargement of lymph nodes, fever, and lymphadenopathy. The disease primarily affects the conjunctiva and the pharynx. Pharyngoconjunctival fever is defined as a viral infectious disease resulting in infection located in the pharynx or conjunctiva, caused by Human adenovirus 3 or Human adenovirus 7. These viruses are transmitted by the droplet spread of respiratory secretions or by fomites. The infection is characterized by symptoms such as fever, lymphadenopathy of the neck, and headache. Furthermore, pharyngoconjunctival fever is also known by its exact synonyms, Adenoviral pharyngoconjunctivitis and pharyngo-conjunctival fever.

Familial combined hyperlipidemia is a type of familial hyperlipidemia. It has exact synonyms including familial multiple lipoprotein-type hyperlipidemia, hyperbetalipoproteinemia with prebetalipoproteinemia, mixed hyperlipidemia, and type IIb hyperlipoproteinemia.

Fox Fordyce disease is a type of sweat gland disease that is characterized by dilatation of the follicular infundibulum with hyperkeratosis, acanthosis, and spongiosis with perifollicular inflammation leading to hair loss. It has symptoms such as flesh-colored papules with hair loss and pruritus, especially of the axilla. This condition also features acanthosis nigricans. Fox Fordyce disease has the exact synonym "Fox Fordyce disease."

Familial hypercholesterolemia is a type of familial hyperlipidemia characterized by very high levels of low-density lipoprotein (LDL) and early cardiovascular disease. It is also known by several exact synonyms, including Fredrickson type IIa hyperlipoproteinemia, Fredrickson type IIa lipidaemia, familial hyperbetalipoproteinaemia, familial hypercholesteremia, hyperbetalipoproteinemia, and type II hyperlipidemia.
Chronic subinvolution of the uterus is a type of uterine disease, which is defined as the inability of the uterus to return to its pre-gestational size after pregnancy.

Adhesions of the uterus is a type of uterine disease, which is defined as a uterine condition characterized by the presence of scar tissue that attaches the uterus to another structure. It is also exactly synonymous with Band of uterus, Intrauterine adhesions, and Intrauterine synechiae.

Hypoglossal nerve disease is characterized as a condition that intersects with diseases located in the hypoglossal nerve, highlighting its specific nature. It falls under the broader category of glossopharyngeal nerve diseases, indicating a type of disorder affecting the glossopharyngeal nerve but specifically located in the hypoglossal nerve, also known as the twelfth cranial nerve. This disease is defined as a glossopharyngeal nerve disease that is found within the hypoglossal nerve. Furthermore, it is synonymously identified in various ways, including as a disorder of the 12th nerve, disorder of the XII nerve, disorder of the hypoglossal [12th] nerve, and disorder of the hypoglossal nerve, indicating a consistency in its identification across different terminologies.

Lymphogranuloma venereum is a commensal bacterial infectious disease that is synonymous with several terms including Climatic or Tropical Bubo, Durand-Nicolas-Favre disease, Lymphogranuloma inguinale, Poradenitis inguinale, and Strumous bubo. It is defined as an infection located in lymph nodes, caused by Chlamydia trachomatis, and can be transmitted through sexual contact or by fomites. This disease is characterized by inguinal lymphadenitis, abscesses in the groin area, and lymphangitis. As a type of disease, lymphogranuloma venereum is also identified as a form of granuloma inguinale and is associated with symptoms such as lymphangitis and abscess. It is classified based on its material basis in Chlamydia trachomatis and its transmission methods, which include contact transmission and vehicle-borne fomite transmission. Additionally, it is described as sharing similarities with diseases that have their location in the lymph.
Miliaria is a type of sweat gland disease characterized by blocked eccrine sweat glands and ducts. It is also known by its exact synonyms eccrine miliaria, heat rash, and sweat rash.
Tetanic cataract is a type of cataract that is defined as a cataract resulting from hypocalcemia. It is also exactly synonymous with Hypocalcaemic cataract.
Parasitic eyelid infestation, which is a type of blepharitis, has the exact synonym "Parasitic infestation of eyelid."

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:squamous_blepharitis rdfs:subClassOf :blepharitis .
text: squamous blepharitis is a type of blepharitis.

Sweat gland disease is the same as a condition that is both a disease and has a location in the sweat glands, indicating an intersection of attributes. Furthermore, sweat gland disease is classified as a type of skin disease. It is defined as a skin disease that is located in the sweat glands.
Patent ductus arteriosus is a type of congenital heart disease and has the exact synonym Patent ductus Botalli. Additionally, it is relatedly synonymous with ductus arteriosus, Patent.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:extrapyramidal_and_movement_disease rdfs:subClassOf :movement_disease .
text: extrapyramidal and movement disease is a type of movement disease.

Abetalipoproteinemia is a type of autosomal recessive disease and a type of hypolipoproteinemia, which also falls under the category of conditions with a material basis in autosomal recessive inheritance. It is defined as a hypolipoproteinemia characterized by an inability to fully absorb dietary fats, cholesterol, and fat-soluble vitamins. This condition arises from an autosomal recessive disorder of lipid metabolism due to a mutation in the microsomal triglyceride transfer protein that is essential for the transport of lipids and the secretion of beta-lipoproteins. Abetalipoproteinemia is exactly synonymous with familial hypobetalipoproteinemia and microsomal triglyceride transfer protein deficiency disease. Additionally, it has an exact match with the MESH identifier D000012.

Scleroperikeratitis is a type of scleritis, also known exactly as Scleritis with corneal involvement. It is characterized by inflammation of the anterior sclera, leading to subsequent inflammation of the adjacent cornea. This condition exhibits symptoms such as inflammation, pain, photophobia, a bloodshot eye, splitting of the urinary stream, and anterior scleral inflammation. Moreover, scleroperikeratitis is defined by its symptoms, which include pain, red eyes, photophobia, tearing, and blurry vision. It may progress to sclerosing keratitis as the inflammation leads to opacification of the anterior corneal stroma, resulting in subsequent vision loss. The cause of scleroperikeratitis is severe anterior scleritis, which can be triggered by autoimmune diseases, connective tissue diseases, and infections.

Acute closed angle glaucoma, also known exactly as acute angle-closure glaucoma, is a type of primary angle closure glaucoma. This condition is characterized by an acute closure of the anterior chamber angle due to an intrinsic defect, which blocks aqueous outflow and suddenly elevates intraocular pressure, thereby threatening further optic nerve damage and visual field loss. Symptoms of acute closed angle glaucoma include sudden pain, redness, headache, and blurry vision with haloes around lights. Additionally, it exhibits symptoms such as bloodshot eye, headache, and acute pain, and it has the feature of ocular hypertension. Acute closed angle glaucoma can be triggered by an exacerbation of chronic primary angle-closure glaucoma, typically induced by medications or states that dilate the eyes, thus narrowing the anterior chamber angle and blocking any aqueous outflow.

Trochlear nerve disease is equivalent to a condition that intersects with diseases located at least in the trochlear nerve. It is categorized as a type of cranial nerve disease. Furthermore, trochlear nerve disease is precisely synonymous with superior oblique muscle innervation disorder, trochlear nerve disorder, and disorder of trochlear nerve.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:facial_neuralgia rdfs:subClassOf :facial_nerve_disease .
text: facial neuralgia is a type of facial nerve disease.
Multiple cranial nerve palsy, which is a type of glossopharyngeal nerve disease, has an exact synonym: Multiple cranial nerve palsies.

Focal labyrinthitis is a specific type of labyrinthitis which is a disease located in the vestibular labyrinth. It is defined as a labyrinthitis that is an infectious inflammatory disease affecting a circumscribed area of either the vestibular or the cochlear portion of the labyrinth, or both. This condition is caused by chronic suppurative otitis media, mastoiditis, or cholesteatoma. Focal labyrinthitis is also exactly known as Circumscribed labyrinthitis.
Hypoactive sexual desire disorder is a type of psychosexual disorder and is exactly synonymous with the lack or loss of sexual desire.

Hypolipoproteinemia is a type of lipid metabolism disorder and is defined as a lipid metabolism disorder characterized by unusually low levels of fats in the blood. It has the exact synonym Hypolipoproteinaemia and is also related to the synonym Lipoprotein deficiencies.

Tangier disease is a type of hypolipoproteinemia and has the definition of a hypolipoproteinemia that is characterized by markedly reduced levels of plasma high-density lipoproteins, resulting in tissue accumulation of cholesterol esters. This disease has its material basis in homozygous or compound heterozygous mutation in the ABCA1 gene on chromosome 9q31. It has exact synonyms such as familial alpha-lipoprotein deficiency and familial high-density lipoprotein deficiency. Additionally, Tangier disease has an exact match with MESH:D013631.
Sick sinus syndrome is a type of sinoatrial node disease and has an exact synonym, which is sinus node infection. Additionally, it has an exact match with MESH:D012804.

Polyneuropathy is a type of peripheral nervous system disease and is also characterized as a condition that at least manifests symptoms of some peripheral muscle weakness. It is defined as a peripheral system disease characterized by damage affecting peripheral nerves (peripheral neuropathy) in roughly the same areas on both sides of the body, featuring symptoms such as weakness, numbness, pins-and-needles sensation, and burning pain.

Bird fancier's lung, also known as Avian hypersensitivity pneumonitis, Bird-fancier's lung, Bird-fanciers' lung, bird breeder's lung, bird fancier lung, pigeon breeder's lung, and poultry worker's lung, is a type of extrinsic allergic alveolitis. This condition is characterized by a variety of symptoms including fever, cough, acute dyspnea, dyspnea, and malaise. It is defined as an extrinsic allergic alveolitis caused by inhalation of antigens from avian excreta, leading to an abrupt onset of dyspnea, cough, malaise, and fever following exposure to the antigen.
Squamous cell papilloma is a type of papilloma and is exactly synonymous with Epidermoid papilloma.

Hypobetalipoproteinemia is a type of hypolipoproteinemia and is characterized by permanently low levels of apolipoprotein B and LDL cholesterol, which results from an impaired ability to absorb and transport fats. It is also exactly synonymous with Hypo-beta-lipoproteinemia.

White piedra is a type of superficial mycosis and is defined as a superficial mycosis that is a superficial fungal infection of the hair shaft caused by Trichosporon beigelii, where infected hairs develop soft greyish-white nodules along the shaft. Additionally, white piedra has an exact synonym, Tinea blanca.
Red green color blindness is a type of color blindness that is also known exactly as Deutan defect, Deuteranopia, and Reduced red-green discrimination.
Norum disease is a type of hypolipoproteinemia and is also known as Lecithin Cholesterol Acyltransferase Deficiency or Lecithin Acyltransferase Deficiency.
Red color blindness, a type of color blindness, is exactly synonymous with both Protan defect and Protanopia.

Achromatopsia is a type of color blindness, which is defined as a congenital cone color vision disorder characterized by the inability to perceive color and to achieve satisfactory visual acuity at high light levels; this condition has a material basis in autosomal recessive inheritance. Additionally, achromatopsia has exact synonyms, including ACHM and Monochromatism.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:acquired_color_blindness rdfs:subClassOf :color_blindness ;
    :has_exact_synonym "acquired color vision deficiencies"@en,
        "acquired color vision deficiency"@en,
        "acquired colour blindness"@en,
        "acquired colour vision deficiencies"@en,
        "acquired colour vision deficiency"@en .
text: Acquired color blindness, a type of color blindness, is also precisely known by several other names: acquired color vision deficiencies, acquired color vision deficiency, acquired colour blindness, acquired colour vision deficiencies, and acquired colour vision deficiency.
A lumbosacral plexus lesion, which has the exact synonym "Lumbosacral plexus lesions," is a type of peripheral nervous system disease.

Somatization disorder, also known as Briquet's disorder or Somatisation disorder, is a type of somatoform disorder. It is defined as a somatoform disorder that involves persistent complaints of varied physical symptoms that have no identifiable physical origin. Additionally, it is related to the term Polysomatising disorder.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:irregular_astigmatism rdfs:subClassOf :astigmatism .
text: irregular astigmatism is a type of astigmatism.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:pseudopapilledema rdfs:subClassOf :visual_pathway_disease .
text: pseudopapilledema is a type of visual pathway disease.
Bacterial esophagitis is a type of esophagitis and a type of bacterial infectious disease that has a material basis in some bacteria.

Eosinophilic esophagitis is a type of esophagitis and also a type of condition that at least has the symptom of some inflammation. It is defined as an esophagitis characterized by inflammation involving eosinophils located in the esophagus.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:necrotizing_ulcerative_gingivitis rdfs:subClassOf :gingivitis ;
    :has_exact_synonym "ANUG"@en,
        "Angina - Vincents"@en,
        "Vincent angina"@en,
        "Vincent's angina"@en,
        "Vincent's angina - pharyngitis"@en,
        "Vincent's disease"@en,
        "Vincent's infection, any site"@en,
        "acute necrotising ulcerative gingivitis"@en,
        "acute necrotising ulcerative gingivostomatitis"@en,
        "acute necrotizing ulcerative gingivitis"@en,
        "acute necrotizing ulcerative gingivostomatitis"@en,
        "acute ulceromembranous gingivitis"@en,
        "early acute necrotising gingivitis"@en,
        "trench mouth"@en .
text: Necrotizing ulcerative gingivitis is a type of gingivitis that has several exact synonyms, including ANUG, Angina - Vincents, Vincent angina, Vincent's angina, Vincent's angina - pharyngitis, Vincent's disease, Vincent's infection at any site, acute necrotising ulcerative gingivitis, acute necrotising ulcerative gingivostomatitis, acute necrotizing ulcerative gingivitis, acute necrotizing ulcerative gingivostomatitis, acute ulceromembranous gingivitis, early acute necrotising gingivitis, and trench mouth.

Lacrimal duct obstruction is a type of lacrimal apparatus disease and has exact synonyms including Blocked lacrimal canaliculus, Obstruction of lacrimal canaliculus, and Obstruction of lacrimal ducts.

Visual pathway disease is the same as a disease that intersects with an ailment located at least in the optic tract. It is a type of eye disease. Moreover, visual pathway disease is defined as an eye disease that affects the neural pathway from the optic nerve to the visual cortex, through which light is interpreted as an image.
Facial paralysis, which has the exact synonym Facial Palsy, is a type of facial nerve disease.

Amenorrhea is a type of female reproductive system disease characterized by the absence of menstruation. It is exactly synonymous with "absence of menstruation" and "amenia." Additionally, it has an exact match with the MESH identifier D000568.

Urinary schistosomiasis is a type of schistosomiasis and also a type of bladder disease, specifically a disease that affects the urinary bladder. It is defined as a schistosomiasis involving a parasitic infection of the urinary tract caused by the digenetic trematode Schistosoma haematobium. This infection leads to cystitis, ureteritis, fibrosis of the bladder, and haematuria, which can progress to bladder cancer. Urinary schistosomiasis is known by several exact synonyms: Schistosoma Hematobium Infection, Schistosoma haematobium, Schistosoma hematobium infectious disease, Schistosomiasis due to schistosoma haematobium, Schistosomiasis of bladder, Vesical schistosomiasis, bladder Schistosomiasis, and cystitis with bilharziasis. Additionally, it has a related synonym, which is Schistosoma haematobium infection.

Benign paroxysmal positional vertigo is a type of peripheral vertigo that is defined as a peripheral vertigo characterized by episodic vertigo followed by gait imbalance and oscillopsia with profound bilateral vestibular loss despite normal hearing. It also has exact synonyms including benign paroxysmal positional nystagmus and benign recurrent vertigo.
Acute gonococcal salpingitis is a type of acute salpingitis and is exactly synonymous with Gonococcal salpingitis, specified as acute.
Acute gonococcal prostatitis is a type of prostatitis and is exactly synonymous with Gonococcal prostatitis.

CADASIL is a type of leukodystrophy that is defined as a leukodystrophy characterized by recurrent subcortical ischemic stroke and cognitive impairment. It is precisely synonymous with cerebral autosomal dominant arteriopathy with subcortical infarcts and leukoencephalopathy, as well as hereditary multi-infarct dementia.
Bladder neck obstruction is a type of bladder disease and is exactly synonymous with obstruction of bladder neck or vesicourethral orifice.
Interstitial cystitis is a type of cystitis and it is exactly synonymous with ulcerative cystitis.

Schistosomiasis is a type of parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease, which is defined as a parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease that involves infection of the intestine, urinary tract, skin, liver, and spleen caused by multiple species of the trematode fluke of the genus Schistosoma. It is a condition that fundamentally has a material basis in some schistosoma. This disease is characterized by a variety of symptoms including hematuria, abdominal pain, nausea, hepatomegaly, rash, splenomegaly, diarrhea, fever, chills, and malaise. Additionally, the symptoms also encompass liver and spleen enlargement, myalgia, and rash.

Uterine corpus epithelioid leiomyoma is a type of uterine fibroid that has at least one symptom of necrosis and is a disease located in the body of the uterus. It is defined as an uterine fibroid characterized by the presence of round epithelioid, rhabdoid, and large vacuolated cells intermingled with spindled cells, clear or eosinophilic cytoplasm, and the absence of prominent nuclear atypia, tumor cell necrosis, and mitotic figures.

Uterine corpus dissecting leiomyoma is a type of uterine fibroid and falls under the category of diseases located in the body of the uterus. It is defined as a uterine fibroid characterized by the presence of intramural tearing.
Uterus interstitial leiomyoma, also known exactly as intramural leiomyoma of the uterus, is a type of uterine fibroid. It is defined as a uterine fibroid that is located within the myometrium.

Uterine corpus myxoid leiomyoma is a type of uterine fibroid that is characterized by islands of smooth muscle in myxoid connective tissue. These islands contain large vessels and are notable for their lack of infiltrative growth, atypia, or mitotic activity. Additionally, this condition is a type of disease located in some parts of the body of the uterus.
Uterine corpus lipoleiomyoma is a type of uterine fibroid and is characterized by the presence of adipocytes. It is also a type of condition that occurs in the body of the uterus.

Uterine corpus bizarre leiomyoma, also known exactly as uterine Corpus Symplastic leiomyoma, is a type of uterine benign neoplasm, leiomyoma, and something that at least derives from some smooth muscle cell, and is also a type of something that at least has its disease location in some body of the uterus. It is defined as an uterine benign neoplasm characterized by large, atypical nuclei in otherwise normal appearing leiomyoma and rare or absent mitotic figures, and it has a material basis in smooth muscle cells.

A nuclear senile cataract is a type of senile cataract that is defined as a senile cataract characterized by the opacification of the lens nucleus, caused by changes related to aging. It is also exactly synonymous with Senile nuclear cataract and Senile nuclear sclerosis.

Morgagni cataract is a type of senile cataract and is defined as a senile cataract characterized by dense white opacification of the lens and milky fluid in the lens capsule, resulting in the dense nucleus of the lens sinking in the surrounding fluid. It represents the late stage of senile cataracts and is attributed to a multifactorial etiology related to aging. Additionally, Morgagni cataract is exactly synonymous with hypermature cataract.
Chronic orbital inflammation is a type of orbital disease and is exactly synonymous with chronic inflammation of the orbit.

Female breast lower outer quadrant cancer is a type of female breast cancer, which is defined as a female breast cancer that is located in the lower-outer quadrant of the breast. Moreover, it has the exact synonym "malignant neoplasm of lower-outer quadrant of female breast."
Peptic esophagitis is a type of esophagitis and has exact synonyms including Peptic reflux disease, Reflux oesophagitis, and reflux esophagitis.

Parasitic infectious disease is a type of disease caused by an infectious agent and is characterized by a disease carried out by a parasite, which is a pathogen that simultaneously injures and derives sustenance from its host. This type of disease is also exactly synonymous with Ectoparasitic disease and parasitemia.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:primary_lacrimal_atrophy rdfs:subClassOf :lacrimal_apparatus_disease .
text: primary lacrimal atrophy is a type of lacrimal apparatus disease.

Cleidocranial dysplasia is a type of autosomal dominant disease and osteochondrodysplasia, which also falls under the category of conditions that have a material basis in autosomal dominant inheritance. It is defined as an osteochondrodysplasia characterized by mutations in the RUNX2 gene, leading to undeveloped or absent clavicles and delayed closing of fontanels in the skull. Furthermore, cleidocranial dysplasia is precisely known as Marie-Sainton Disease and cleidocranial dysostosis.

Small intestine lymphoma is a type of lymphoma, which is also a type of small intestine cancer, and it is a type of condition that at least has a material basis in some lymphocyte. Moreover, small intestine lymphoma has the exact synonym small intestinal Lymphoma.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:contact_blepharoconjunctivitis rdfs:subClassOf :blepharoconjunctivitis .
text: contact blepharoconjunctivitis is a type of blepharoconjunctivitis.

Lacrimal apparatus disease is the same as a disease that intersects with at least one disease that has its location in the lacrimal apparatus. It is a type of eye disease. Moreover, lacrimal apparatus disease is defined as an eye disease that affects the lacrimal apparatus (the lacrimal gland and its related structures), which moisten and drain the eye.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:rubeosis_iridis rdfs:subClassOf :retinal_disease .
text: rubeosis iridis is a type of retinal disease.
A thoracic aortic aneurysm is a type of aortic aneurysm that is defined as an aortic aneurysm located in the thoracic aorta.

A splenic artery aneurysm is identical to an intersection of a vascular disease and a disease that is located at least in the splenic artery. Additionally, a splenic artery aneurysm is a type of artery disease.

Alcoholic liver cirrhosis is a type of liver cirrhosis and is a condition that at least has alcohol as a disease driver. It is exactly synonymous with Alcoholic Cirrhosis, Alcoholic cirrhosis of liver, Laennec's cirrhosis, Laennec's cirrhosis, alcoholic, and Portal cirrhosis.

Brucella canis brucellosis is a type of brucellosis, which fundamentally has a material basis in Brucella canis. It is characterized by a variety of symptoms including weakness, weight loss, headache, splenomegaly, and fever. Moreover, Brucella canis brucellosis is defined as a brucellosis that involves an infection caused by Brucella canis in dogs and humans, manifesting symptoms such as fever, sweats, weakness, weight loss, headache, lymphadenopathy, and splenomegaly.

Tietze's syndrome is synonymous with several terms: Costalchondritis, Costochondral junction syndrome, Costochondritis, Slipping rib syndrome, and Tietze's disease. It also has a related synonym: Tietze syndrome. This syndrome is identified as a type of cartilage disease and falls under the category of syndromes. It is equivalent to an intersection of a syndrome and a disease that specifically affects the costochondral joint.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:algoneurodystrophy rdfs:subClassOf :complex_regional_pain_syndrome .
text: algoneurodystrophy is a type of complex regional pain syndrome.

Folic acid deficiency anemia is a type of nutritional deficiency disease characterized by a decrease in red blood cells due to a lack of folate. This condition has its material basis in insufficient folic acid in the diet, hemolytic anemia, alcoholism, and/or certain medicines. It is also exactly synonymous with Folate deficiency anaemia, Folate deficiency anemia, Folate-deficiency anaemia, Folate-deficiency anemia, Folate-deficient megaloblastic anaemia, and Folic acid deficiency anaemia.
A malignant parietal pleura tumor is a type of pleural cancer and is also known as primary malignant neoplasm of parietal pleura.
A malignant visceral pleura tumor, which is a type of pleural cancer, has the exact synonym of primary malignant neoplasm of visceral pleura.

Aorta atresia is a type of aortic disease characterized by an absence of an opening from the left ventricle of the heart into the aorta. It is exactly synonymous with both "Atresia and stenosis of aorta" and "Congenital atresia and stenosis of aorta."
POEMS syndrome is a type of blood protein disease that is characterized by polyneuropathy, organomegaly, endocrinopathy, monoclonal gammopathy, and skin changes, especially hyperpigmentation.
Residual stage angle closure glaucoma is a type of primary angle closure glaucoma and it is exactly synonymous with Residual stage of angle-closure glaucoma.

Autoimmune polyendocrine syndrome is a type of autoimmune disease of the endocrine system, characterized by abnormal functioning of the immune system that causes auto-reactivity against endocrine organs. It is also exactly synonymous with Autoimmune polyglandular failure, Lloyd's syndrome, and autoimmune polyendocrinopathy.
Bipolar I disorder, a type of bipolar disorder, is characterized by at least one manic or mixed episode.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:neonatal_myasthenia_gravis rdfs:subClassOf :myasthenia_gravis .
text: neonatal myasthenia gravis is a type of myasthenia gravis.

Phaeohyphomycosis is a primary systemic mycosis characterized by infections that can impact various parts of the body, including subcutaneous tissues, the brain, sinuses, lungs, and the peritoneal cavity. It is caused by a variety of dematiacious fungi, notably including Exophiala dermatitidis, Phialophora, Curvularia hawaiiensis, Exserohilum, Cladophialophora bantiana, Phaeoannellomyces, Aureobasidium, Cladosporium cladosporoides, Alternaria, and Rhinocladiella mackenziei. These infections commonly result in the formation of subcutaneous abscesses, which may arise at the site of minor trauma and can occur in both immunosuppressed and immunocompetent individuals. The disease is known to manifest symptoms such as abscesses and affects multiple locations, including the skin zone, brain, peritoneal cavity, paranasal sinus, and lung. Phaeohyphomycosis is also referred to by its exact synonyms, "Infection by dematiacious fungi" and "phaehyphomycosis."

Primary Angle Closure Glaucoma is a type of Angle Closure Glaucoma and is also precisely known as Primary Angle Closure Glaucoma. It is characterized by a closure of the anterior chamber angle due to an intrinsic defect, resulting in blocked aqueous outflow, elevated intraocular pressure, optic nerve damage, and visual field loss. The condition exhibits symptoms such as pain, loss of vision, bloodshot eyes, and headaches. It also has features like ocular hypertension. Furthermore, Primary Angle Closure Glaucoma can be caused by anatomically narrow angles, defects in the trabecular meshwork, and iris abnormalities. It has a strong genetic component. The symptoms also include progressive peripheral vision loss, decreased vision, and in acute cases, pain, redness, and headache.

Paraurethral gland cancer is the same as a condition that is both a cancer and a disease located in the paraurethral gland. It is defined as a female reproductive organ cancer located in the paraurethral glands. Additionally, paraurethral gland cancer is precisely synonymous with malignant tumor of the paraurethral gland, highlighting its nature as a type of female reproductive organ cancer.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:iritis rdfs:subClassOf :iris_disease .
text: iritis is a type of iris disease.
Acute poststreptococcal glomerulonephritis is a type of glomerulonephritis and has the exact synonym Post-Streptococcal Glomerulonephritis.
Acute diffuse nephritis is a type of diffuse glomerulonephritis and is exactly synonymous with acute Diffuse Glomerulonephritis.

Plasmodium falciparum malaria is identical to an intersection of something that is malaria and something that at least has a material basis in some plasmodium falciparum. It is a type of malaria and also a type of condition that at least has a material basis in some Plasmodium falciparum. Plasmodium falciparum malaria is defined as a severe form of the disease caused by the parasite Plasmodium falciparum, characterized by irregular recurrence of paroxysms and prolonged or continuous fever. Furthermore, Plasmodium falciparum malaria is exactly synonymous with Malaria fever, subtertian; falciparum malaria; and malignant tertian fever.

Blackwater fever is a type of malaria and has a definition as a malaria that presents as a rare febrile complication of repeated malarial attacks characterized by intravascular hemolysis, hemoglobinuria, and kidney failure, resulting from destruction of red blood cells caused by heavy parasitization with Plasmodium falciparum or Plasmodium vivax. It has exact synonyms including Black water fever, Hemoglobinuric malaria, and Malarial Hemoglobinuria.

Cerebral malaria is a type of malaria that involves neurologic damage resulting from the blockage of the blood vessels, caused due to the infection of the red blood cells by Plasmodium species. This type of malaria is also known as Malarial encephalitis and is a disease that has its location in the cerebrum.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:anterior_uveitis rdfs:subClassOf :panuveitis .
text: anterior uveitis is a type of panuveitis.
Vestibular nystagmus is a type of globe disease and is exactly synonymous with Nystagmus associated with disorder of the vestibular system.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:geniculate_ganglionitis rdfs:subClassOf :facial_nerve_disease .
text: geniculate ganglionitis is a type of facial nerve disease.

Glucocorticoid remediable aldosteronism (GRA), also known exactly as GRS, familial hyperaldosteronism type I, and glucocorticoid-suppressible hyperaldosteronism, is a type of primary hyperaldosteronism. It is characterized by variably expressed and severe hypertension, hyperaldosteronism, and abnormal adrenal steroid production, which improve with exogenous glucocorticoid administration. This condition has a material basis in a chimeric gene formed of the CYP11B2 and CYP11B1 genes on chromosome 8q24.3.

Toxic labyrinthitis is a type of labyrinthitis that primarily arises from alcohol or other ototoxic substances, which are harmful to the inner ear. This condition is characterized as being induced by the ingestion of alcohol, drugs, or the inhalation of substances toxic to the inner ear. The range of ototoxic substances includes drugs such as aminoglycosides, furosemide, ethacrynic acid, acetylsalicyclic acid (also known as aspirin), amiodarone, quinine, cisplatinum, barbiturates, along with medications used for treating Alzheimer's, anticonvulsants, antidepressants, and anxiolytics.

Epicondylitis is a type of bone inflammation disease defined as a bone inflammation disease that results in inflammation located in the epicondyle. It is also precisely known as lateral epicondylitis, andrel epicondylitis, archer's elbow, golfer's elbow, hockey elbow, and medial epicondylitis. Additionally, epicondylitis is relatedly referred to as shooter's elbow and tennis elbow.
Root caries is a type of dental caries, which also has exact synonyms such as Cementum caries and Dental caries of root surface.

Renal artery atheroma is the same as something that intersects with something that has atherosclerosis and something that is a disease located in the renal artery. It is a type of atherosclerosis as well as a type of renal artery disease. Moreover, renal artery atheroma has exact synonyms, including Atherosclerosis of the renal artery and renal atherosclerosis.

Boutonneuse fever is a type of spotted fever and is also known as African tick typhus, Rickettsia conorii spotted fever, South African tick-bite fever, Kenya tick typhus, and Marseilles fever. It is caused by Rickettsia conorii and transmitted by the dog tick (Rhipicephalus sanguineus) and through tick-borne transmission. The disease is characterized by symptoms such as fever, maculopapular rash, and eschar. The infection specifically has symptoms like fever, eschar (usually single), regional adenopathy, and a maculopapular rash on extremities. Additionally, Boutonneuse fever is relatedly referred to as Boutonneuse disease, Conor and Bruch's disease, Kenya fever, Kenyan tick typhus, Mediterranean spotted fever, and Mediterranean tick fever.
Infertility due to extratesticular cause, which is a type of male infertility, has the exact synonym "Infertility due to extratesticular causes."
Acquired gastric outlet stenosis is a type of pyloric stenosis and has exact synonyms, including acquired hypertrophic pyloric stenosis and adult hypertrophic pyloric stenosis.
De Quervain disease is a type of arthropathy and it has exact synonyms such as Radial styloid tenosynovitis and Tenosynovitis, de Quervain's.

Anus cancer is the same as something that is both cancer and a disease, and it is located in the anus. It is a type of anus disease as well as a type of large intestine cancer. Anus cancer is defined as a large intestine cancer that is located in the anus. Additionally, anus cancer has exact synonyms: anal cancer and malignant anal tumor.
Median rhomboid glossitis is a type of glossitis and it is exactly synonymous with Persistent tuberculum impar.

Toxic Shock Syndrome (TSS), also known as toxic shock, is a commensal bacterial infectious disease characterized by a variety of symptoms and phenotypes. It results from an infection that has a material basis in either Streptococcus pyogenes or Staphylococcus aureus, both of which produce toxins that are absorbed systemically, leading to the systemic manifestations of the disease. The intersection of these two bacteria is crucial for understanding the etiology of Toxic Shock Syndrome. It is also noted for causing abnormalities of the nervous system as part of its phenotype. Symptoms of Toxic Shock Syndrome include fever, rash, hypotension, shock, skin desquamation, headache, diarrhea, vomiting, and multiorgan failure. Additionally, it presents with nonfocal neurologic abnormalities, highlighting the broad impact this condition can have on the body.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:multiple_symmetric_lipomatosis rdfs:subClassOf :lipomatosis ;
    :has_exact_synonym "LIPODYSTROPHY, CEPHALOTHORACIC"@en,
        "LIPOMATOSIS, FAMILIAL BENIGN CERVICAL"@en,
        "Launois-Bensaude's lipomatosis"@en,
        "Madelung's neck"@en,
        "cervical Symmetrical Lipomatosis"@en,
        "multiple symmetrical lipomatosis"@en .
text: Multiple symmetric lipomatosis is a type of lipomatosis. It is also known exactly as lipodystrophy, cephalothoracic, lipomatosis, familial benign cervical, Launois-Bensaude's lipomatosis, Madelung's neck, cervical symmetrical lipomatosis, and multiple symmetrical lipomatosis.

Familial lipoprotein lipase deficiency is a type of autosomal recessive disease and familial chylomicronemia syndrome. It is also considered a type of condition that at least has a material basis in autosomal recessive inheritance. This familial hyperlipemia is characterized by a deficiency of the enzyme lipoprotein lipase, leading to the accumulation of chylomicrons and an increased plasma concentration of triglycerides. The condition is exactly synonymous with several terms, including Fredrickson type I hyperlipoproteinemia, Fredrickson type I lipaemia, familial LPL deficiency, familial chylomicronemia syndrome, familial hyperlipoproteinemia type I, hypercholesterinaemic xanthomatosis, hyperchylomicronemia, and mixed hyperglyceridemia.
Bacteriuria is a type of urinary system disease, defined as a condition where there is the presence of bacteria in urine.
Blue toe syndrome is a type of cholesterol embolism and is a condition that occurs in the foot, indicating that it is a type of disease located in at least some part of the foot.
Abducens nerve neoplasm, which is a type of cranial nerve malignant neoplasm, has exact synonyms that include VIth Cranial nerve tumors and neoplasm of abducens nerve.
A lateral cystocele is a type of prolapse of the female genital organ, which is defined as the descent of the bladder causing a bulge in the anterolateral vaginal walls.

Midline cystocele is a type of prolapse of the female genital organ, which is defined as a prolapse of the female genital organ characterized by the descent of the bladder causing a bulge in the midline anterior vaginal wall.

Masters Allen Syndrome is a type of disease affecting the female reproductive system. It is defined as a condition characterized by an excessively mobile uterus, which is secondary to lacerations of the broad and cardinal ligaments. This condition also involves specific tenderness with movement of the cervix and is associated with previous adverse obstetric events, such as premature maternal voluntary efforts, precipitate delivery, and forceps delivery. Furthermore, Masters Allen Syndrome is exactly synonymous with Broad Ligament Laceration Syndrome.

Anus lymphoma is a type of lymphoma and a type of anus cancer. It is also a type of condition that intersects with something that has at least a material basis in some lymphocytes and something that at least has the location of some lymphoid tissue disease. Moreover, anus lymphoma has the exact synonym "Lymphoma of anus."
Ovarian dysfunction, which is a type of ovarian disease, is characterized by irregular or absent ovulation.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:pulp_erosion rdfs:subClassOf :tooth_erosion .
text: pulp erosion is a type of tooth erosion.

Malignant anus melanoma is a type of anus cancer and a type of melanoma, which is a subtype of something that derives from melanocytes. Furthermore, it has exact synonyms which include anal melanoma and malignant melanoma of the anus.

Ureterolithiasis is a type of ureteral disease characterized by the formation of stoney concentrations in the ureter. It has exact synonyms including Ureteric calculus, Ureteric stone, and calculus of ureter.
Gyrate atrophy is a type of choroid disease and has exact synonyms including Gyrate atrophy of the choroid and/or retina, Ornithinemia with gyrate atrophy, and gyrate atrophy of the retina.

Spinal cord lymphoma is a type of lymphoma, spinal cancer, central nervous system hematologic cancer, and something that at least has a material basis in some lymphocyte. It is defined as a spinal cancer that is located in the spinal cord and derives from lymphocytes. Spinal cord lymphoma is exactly synonymous with Lymphoma of the Spinal Cord and is relatedly synonymous with spinal cord cancer.

Spinal cord melanoma is a type of melanoma, and it is also classified as a type of spinal cancer. Furthermore, it originates from melanocytes and is located specifically in the spinal cord. Additionally, it is exactly synonymous with melanoma of the spinal cord.

Spinal cord sarcoma is a type of sarcoma, spinal cancer, and a disease that originates from some embryonic cell metazoa and has its location in the spinal cord. Additionally, it is exactly synonymous with sarcoma of the spinal cord.
Acute retrobulbar neuritis is a type of optic neuritis and has the exact synonym "Retrobulbar neuritis."

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:obstructive_hydrocephalus rdfs:subClassOf :hydrocephalus .
text: obstructive hydrocephalus is a type of hydrocephalus.
Bilateral hyperactive labyrinth is a type of labyrinthine dysfunction and has exact synonyms including hyperactive bilateral labyrinthine dysfunction and hyperactive labyrinth, bilateral.

Choroid disease is the same as something that is an intersection of a disease and something that, at the very least, has a disease located in the optic choroid. It is a type of uveal disease. Moreover, choroid disease is defined as an uveal disease that is located in the choroid.

Rheumatic congestive heart failure is a type of congestive heart failure and also falls under the category of conditions that at least have the symptom of some heart failure. It is exactly synonymous with both Congestive rheumatic heart failure and Rheumatic heart failure.
Central neurocytoma, which is a type of cerebral ventricle cancer, has an exact synonym: Neurolipocytoma.
Von Hippel Lindau disease is a type of hemangioblastoma and has exact synonyms including Hippel Lindau syndrome and von Hippel-Lindau syndrome.

Selective IgG deficiency disease is a type of dysgammaglobulinemia that is characterized by an isolated deficiency of an IgG subclass, normal total IgG levels, and a subsequent increased susceptibility to recurrent infections, atopic disease, and autoimmune conditions. It is also known by several exact synonyms, including Immunoglobulin G subclass deficiency, Selective IgG Immunodeficiency, Selective Immunoglobulin G Subclass deficiency, Selective deficiency of IgG, and Selective immunoglobulin G deficiency.

Congenital hypogammaglobulinemia is a type of physical disorder and a type of B cell deficiency. It is also a type of condition that has its basis in some abnormality of prenatal development or birth. Moreover, congenital hypogammaglobulinemia has an exact synonym: Congenital hypogammaglobulinaemia.

X-linked agammaglobulinemia is a type of agammaglobulinemia, which is also a form of X-linked recessive disease. This condition is specifically characterized by having a material basis in some form of X-linked recessive inheritance. It is defined as an agammaglobulinemia that results from a mutation in the Bruton's tyrosine kinase (BTK) gene on the X chromosome, leading to X-linked agammaglobulinemia type 1. This immunodeficiency is marked by the failure to produce mature B lymphocytes and is associated with a failure of immunoglobulin heavy chain rearrangement. Furthermore, X-linked agammaglobulinemia is known by several exact synonyms including BTK deficiency, Bruton agammaglobulinemia tyrosine kinase deficiency, Bruton disease, Bruton's Sex-Linked Agammaglobulinemia, Bruton's agammaglobulinaemia, Bruton's type agammaglobulinemia, and Bruton-type agammaglobulinemia.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:calcific_tendinitis rdfs:subClassOf :tendinitis .
text: calcific tendinitis is a type of tendinitis.

Alcoholic neuropathy is a type of inflammatory and toxic neuropathy, and it is also a type of condition that has alcohol as at least one disease driver. Furthermore, alcoholic neuropathy is precisely synonymous with Alcohol-related polyneuropathy and Alcoholic polyneuropathy. Additionally, it has an exact match with MESH:D020269.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:polyneuropathy_due_to_drug rdfs:subClassOf :inflammatory_and_toxic_neuropathy .
text: polyneuropathy due to drug is a type of inflammatory and toxic neuropathy.

Frozen shoulder, also known precisely as adhesive capsulitis of shoulder or adhesions-capsulitis of the shoulder, is a type of connective tissue disease. It is characterized by a restriction of both active and passive range of motion located in the scapulohumeral joint and exhibits symptoms such as pain and a restricted range of motion. Additionally, frozen shoulder is associated with at least some pain, making it a condition that falls under the category of diseases with pain as a symptom.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:bicipital_tenosynovitis rdfs:subClassOf :tenosynovitis .
text: bicipital tenosynovitis is a type of tenosynovitis.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:posterior_dislocation_of_lens rdfs:subClassOf :globe_disease .
text: posterior dislocation of lens is a type of globe disease.
Adult dermatomyositis is a type of dermatomyositis and also a type of condition that begins during adult onset. Additionally, it has an exact synonym: adult onset dermatomyositis.

Childhood type dermatomyositis is a type of dermatomyositis and also falls under the category of conditions that typically begin in childhood. It is exactly synonymous with both Juvenile dermatomyositis and Childhood Dermatomyositis.

Hypophosphatasia is a type of autosomal genetic disease and a syndrome that fundamentally has a material basis in autosomal inheritance. It is characterized by a disruption of the mineralization of bones and teeth, which is caused by mutations in the ALPL gene located on chromosome 1p36.12. Furthermore, hypophosphatasia is precisely synonymous with childhood hypophosphatasia, deficiency of alkaline phosphatase, and childhood hypophospatasia.

Dihydropyrimidine dehydrogenase deficiency is a type of purine-pyrimidine metabolic disorder and is defined as an autosomal recessive metabolic disorder characterized by absent or significantly decreased activity of dihydropyrimidine dehydrogenase, an enzyme involved in the metabolism of uracil and thymine. This condition is also exactly synonymous with Dihydrouracil Dehydrogenase deficiency, familial pyrimidinaemia, and thymine-uracilurea.

Renal tubular acidosis is a type of renal tubular transport disease characterized by excess levels of acid in the blood. This condition arises from a failure of the kidneys to appropriately acidify the urine.

Abdominal obesity metabolic syndrome 1 is a type of abdominal obesity metabolic syndrome, characterized by insulin resistance and hyperinsulinemia, dyslipidemia, essential hypertension, abdominal obesity, glucose intolerance or noninsulin-dependent diabetes mellitus, and an increased risk of cardiovascular events. Additionally, it is exactly synonymous with dysmetabolic syndrome X and metabolic syndrome X.

Ochronosis is a type of connective tissue disease that is characterized by a bluish-brown discoloration of connective tissues. This condition develops from the deposition of homogentisic acid and subsequent oxidation and polymerization reactions.
Tracheal calcification is a type of tracheal disease and it is exactly synonymous with Calcification of trachea.
Acute frontal sinusitis is a type of frontal sinusitis defined as a frontal sinusitis that lasts for less than 4 weeks.
Azoospermia, a type of male infertility, is defined as a male infertility disease characterized by the absence of any measurable level of sperm in semen. It has an exact match with MESH:D053713.
Oligospermia is a type of male infertility, defined as a male fertility issue characterized by a low sperm concentration in the ejaculate.

Scleromalacia perforans is a type of scleral disease that is characterized by a painless severe necrotizing scleritis where the sclera is white, avascular, and thin. This condition leads to the sclera becoming so thin that the dark uvea protrudes through the front of the eye, forming a staphyloma, which can result in a loss of vision and the appearance of a dark bulge. Furthermore, scleromalacia perforans exhibits symptoms such as necrosis and loss of vision. It is usually caused by a rare complication of autoimmune diseases like rheumatoid arthritis.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:orbital_cyst rdfs:subClassOf :orbital_disease .
text: orbital cyst is a type of orbital disease.

Gastrointestinal tularemia is the same as something that is an intersection of tularemia and a disease that has its location in the digestive system. It is a type of tularemia as well as a type of gastrointestinal system disease. Gastrointestinal tularemia is characterized by having symptoms such as fever, vomiting, lymphadenitis, chills, and malaise. It is defined as a tularemia that results in the formation of ulcerative lesions located in the gastrointestinal tract, with the infection presenting symptoms including fever, chills, malaise, muscle aches, and vomiting. Additionally, gastrointestinal tularemia is also known by its exact synonyms "Enteric tularemia" and "intestinal tularaemia."

Chronic perichondritis of the pinna is a type of perichondritis of the auricle, which is defined as a perichondritis of the auricle that is persistent and long-lasting. It is also exactly synonymous with chronic pinna perichondritis.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:epiphora_due_to_excess_lacrimation rdfs:subClassOf :excessive_tearing .
text: epiphora due to excess lacrimation is a type of excessive tearing.
Cystoid macular retinal degeneration is a type of degeneration of the macula and posterior pole, and it has an exact synonym, Cystoid macular degeneration of retina.

Chronic purulent otitis media is a type of suppurative otitis media, defined as a suppurative otitis media that is persistent and long-lasting. It is also exactly synonymous with chronic suppurative otitis media.

Chronic atticoantral disease is a type of chronic purulent otitis media, and it is exactly synonymous with chronic atticoantral suppurative otitis media. It is defined as a chronic purulent otitis media which involves perforation in the attic region (pars flaccida of the tympanic membrane) or at the posterosuperior margin, with the in-growth of squamous epithelium into the middle ear. This condition is caused as a result of poor ventilation of the middle ear and episodes of infection.
Pyoureter is a type of ureteral disease, which is exactly synonymous with ureter abscess.

Down syndrome is a type of chromosomal duplication syndrome and is also a type of condition that intersects with having a material basis in some chromosome and duplication. It is defined as a chromosomal disease characterized by flat-looking facial features and weak muscle tone (hypotonia) in infancy, caused by trisomy of all or a critical portion of chromosome 21, and is associated with intellectual disability. Furthermore, Down syndrome has several exact synonyms, including Complete trisomy 21 syndrome, Down's syndrome, Down's syndrome - trisomy 21, Downs syndrome, G Trisomy, and trisomy 21 syndrome.
Vitreoretinal dystrophy is a type of fundus dystrophy and has the exact synonym "Vitreoretinal dystrophies."

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:dystrophies_primarily_involving_the_retinal_pigment_epithelium rdfs:subClassOf :fundus_dystrophy .
text: dystrophies primarily involving the retinal pigment epithelium is a type of fundus dystrophy.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:retinal_dystrophy_in_systemic_or_cerebroretinal_lipidoses rdfs:subClassOf :fundus_dystrophy .
text: retinal dystrophy in systemic or cerebroretinal lipidoses is a type of fundus dystrophy.

Adult Onset Still's Disease is a type of rheumatoid arthritis and also falls under the category of conditions that begin in adulthood. It is defined as a rheumatoid arthritis characterized by high fevers, rash, sore throat, and joint pain. Furthermore, Adult Onset Still's Disease is exactly synonymous with both 'Adult Onset Still's Disease' and 'Adult-onset Still Disease.'

Ureteral disease is the same as something that is an intersection of a disease and something that has a disease located in the ureter. It is a type of urinary system disease. Moreover, ureteral disease is defined as a urinary system disease that is located in the ureter.

Fragile X syndrome is a syndrome and a type of X-linked dominant disease, which essentially has a material basis in some X-linked dominant inheritance. It is defined as a syndrome characterized by moderate to severe mental retardation, macroorchidism, and distinct facial features, including a long face, large ears, and a prominent jaw. This syndrome has its material basis in X-linked inheritance and a loss of FMR1 function. Moreover, Fragile X syndrome is exactly synonymous with Fragile X Mental Retardation Syndrome, Marker X Syndrome, and Martin-Bell Syndrome.

Oral candidiasis is a type of candidiasis and also a type of mouth disease that occurs specifically in the oral cavity. It is defined as a candidiasis involving fungal infection of the mucous membrane of the mouth by Candida species, which is characterized by thick white or cream-colored deposits on inflamed mucosal membranes. Oral candidiasis is known by exact synonyms such as Candidiasis of the mouth, Oral moniliasis, Thrush, oral, and thrush.

Benign neonatal seizures is a type of neonatal period electroclinical syndrome characterized by tonic-clonic seizures in newborns occurring within the first seven days of life and ceasing within the first 15 weeks of life. This syndrome has a material basis in the autosomal dominant inheritance of voltage-gated potassium channels or a chromosomal inversion. It is also precisely known as benign familial neonatal seizures and benign neonatal convulsions.

Pulmonary valve insufficiency is a type of pulmonary valve disease characterized by the pulmonary valve's inability to prevent backflow into the right ventricle. This condition is specifically referred to as a Graham Steell murmur when it is secondary to pulmonary hypertension. It is also known by various exact synonyms, including Pulmonic insufficiency, Pulmonic valve regurgitation, pulmonary incompetence, pulmonary incompetence, non-rheumatic, pulmonary insufficiency following trauma and surgery, pulmonary regurg., and pulmonary regurgitation. Furthermore, pulmonary valve insufficiency is exactly matched with the MESH identifier D011665.
Sclerosing cholangitis is a type of cholangitis and has an exact synonym, fibrosing cholangitis.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:suppurative_cholangitis rdfs:subClassOf :cholangitis .
text: suppurative cholangitis is a type of cholangitis.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:ascending_cholangitis rdfs:subClassOf :cholangitis .
text: ascending cholangitis is a type of cholangitis.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:acute_cholangitis rdfs:subClassOf :cholangitis .
text: acute cholangitis is a type of cholangitis.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:pericholangitis rdfs:subClassOf :cholangitis .
text: pericholangitis is a type of cholangitis.

Atrophic vulva is a type of vulvar disease and it is defined as a vulvar disease characterized by the presence of atrophy, associated with decreased estrogenization. It is also exactly synonymous with Atrophy of vulva.
Shoulder impingement syndrome is a type of arthropathy and has exact synonyms, including Impingement syndrome of shoulder region and Subacromial impingement.

Endocrine pancreas disease is the same as something that is both a disease and has a location in the endocrine pancreas, which is also an intersection of diseases that at least have a location in the endocrine pancreas. It is a specific type of pancreas disease. The definition of endocrine pancreas disease states that it is a pancreas disease located in the endocrine component of the pancreas, consisting of islet cells (islets of Langerhans) that create and release important hormones directly into the bloodstream.
Primary hypertrophic osteoarthropathy is a type of syndrome that has exact synonyms Pachydermoperiostosis of nail and Pachydermoperiostosis syndrome.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:patellofemoral_pain_syndrome rdfs:subClassOf :arthropathy .
text: patellofemoral pain syndrome is a type of arthropathy.

Neurogenic arthropathy is a type of arthropathy and it has exact synonyms such as Arthropathy associated with neurological disorder, Charcot's arthropathy, and Neuropathic arthropathy. Additionally, it has a related synonym, Charcot's joint.

Brawny scleritis is a type of anterior scleritis characterized by painful inflammation and tender nodule formation of the anterior sclera. It exhibits symptoms such as pain, red eyes (bloodshot eye), photophobia (light sensitivity), tearing, blurry vision, and the appearance of eye surface irregularity. Additionally, this condition can be triggered by autoimmune diseases, connective tissue diseases, and infections.

Ebstein anomaly is a type of tricuspid valve disease characterized by a congenital heart defect in which the septal leaflet of the tricuspid valve is displaced towards the apex of the right ventricle of the heart. It is also exactly synonymous with Ebstein's anomaly, Ebstein's anomaly of common atrioventricular valve, Ebstein's anomaly of right atrioventricular valve, and Ebstein's anomaly of tricuspid valve.

Noonan syndrome with multiple lentigines is a type of autosomal dominant disease, a type of RASopathy, and something that at least has a material basis in some autosomal dominant inheritance. It is defined as a RASopathy characterized by autosomal dominant inheritance of brown skin spots called lentigines that are similar to freckles, heart defects, widely spaced eyes, a sunken chest or protruding chest, and short stature. Furthermore, it is known by several exact synonyms, including Capute-Rimoin-Konigsmark-Esterly-Richardson syndrome, Generalized lentiginosis, Gorlin syndrome II, LEOPARD syndrome, Lentiginosis profusa syndrome, Moynahan syndrome, Multiple lentigines syndrome, and Progressive cardiomyopathic lentiginosis.
Vulvar dystrophy is a type of vulvar disease characterized by irregular patchy areas of thickened skin and severe itching. It is also known by the exact synonym Dystrophy of vulva.

Tuberculous empyema is a type of pleural empyema, defined as a pleural empyema that involves the presence of pus in the pleural cavity and calcified visceral pleura. This condition results from a large number of mycobacteria spilling into the pleural space, usually due to the rupture of a cavity or an adjacent parenchymal focus via a bronchopleural fistula.

Skin epithelioid hemangioma is a type of hemangioma, a type of skin benign neoplasm, and also a type of entity that at least derives from some endothelial cell. It has exact synonyms such as Angiolymphoid Cutaneous Hyperplasia and Epithelioid Hemangioma of Skin.

Pleuropneumonia is a type of pneumonia and also a type of condition that at least has the symptom of some inflammation. It is defined as a pneumonia that is accompanied by inflammation of the pleura and accumulation of pus in the pleural space, which is caused by bacteria.
Blindness is a type of eye disease, which is characterized by a lack or loss of vision. It has exact synonyms including vision impairment, vision loss, and visual impairment.

Generalized anxiety disorder is a type of anxiety disorder and is characterized by long-lasting anxiety that is not focused on any one object or situation. It is a type of condition that at least has some anxiety as a symptom.

Marfan syndrome is a type of connective tissue disease that is also classified as a type of aortic disease, eye disease, and involves conditions where at least some diseases have locations in the aorta and eye. It is defined as a connective tissue disease characterized by tall stature, elongated extremities, mitral valve prolapse, aortic dilatation, aortic dissection, and subluxation of the lens. Marfan syndrome is exactly synonymous with Marfan's syndrome and has an exact match with MESH:D008382.

Plasmodium malariae malaria is a type of malaria that is caused by the parasite Plasmodium malariae. This form of malaria is characterized by the recurrence of paroxysms at 72-hour intervals. It is also exactly synonymous with Malaria by Plasmodium malariae and Quartan Malaria.

Mixed malaria is a type of malaria characterized by an infection involving more than one species of Plasmodium simultaneously. It is defined as a malaria that involves infection with more than one species of Plasmodium at the same time. Additionally, mixed malaria is exactly synonymous with both "Malaria fever by more than one parasite" and "malaria by more than one parasite".

Parkinson's disease is a type of synucleinopathy and is defined as a synucleinopathy that has a material basis in the degeneration of the central nervous system, often impairing motor skills, speech, and other functions. It has the exact synonyms Parkinson disease and paralysis agitans.
Postencephalitic Parkinson disease, which is a type of secondary Parkinson disease, is exactly synonymous with postencephalitic parkinsonism.
Estrogen excess is a type of ovarian dysfunction and is defined as an ovarian dysfunction characterized by a higher than normal ratio of estrogen. It is also known as hyperestrogenism.
Suppurative thyroiditis is a type of thyroiditis and has exact synonyms such as Infectious thyroiditis and acute suppurative thyroiditis.
Riedel's fibrosing thyroiditis is a type of thyroiditis, which has the exact synonym Riedel fibrosing thyroiditis.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:acute_thyroiditis rdfs:subClassOf :thyroiditis .
text: acute thyroiditis is a type of thyroiditis.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:corneal_ectasia rdfs:subClassOf :corneal_disease .
text: corneal ectasia is a type of corneal disease.

Systemic primary carnitine deficiency disease is a type of amino acid metabolic disorder defined by defective proteins known as carnitine transporters, which are crucial for bringing carnitine into cells and preventing its escape from the body. This defect hinders the body's ability to utilize fats for energy. The disease is also exactly synonymous with several terms including carnitine transporter deficiency, carnitine uptake defect, deficiency of plasma-membrane carnitine transporter, primary carnitine deficiency, and renal carnitine transport defect.

Norwegian scabies is a type of scabies that is defined as a scabies involving infestation by the human itch mite Sarcoptes scabiei type hominis, particularly in immunocompromised and elderly persons. It is characterized by the formation of vesicles and thick crusts over the skin, accompanied by abundant mites but only slight itching. Moreover, Norwegian scabies is also exactly known as Crusted scabies.

A parietal lobe neoplasm is the same as something that is both a cancer and a disease, with the condition specifically located in the parietal lobe. It is categorized as a type of cerebrum cancer, defined as a cerebrum cancer located in the parietal lobe. Additionally, a parietal lobe neoplasm is exactly synonymous with a malignant neoplasm of the parietal lobe and a tumor of the parietal lobe.
Pyuria is a type of urinary system disease and has the exact synonym "Pus cells in urine."

Thrombophlebitis migrans is a type of thrombophlebitis and is characterized by repeated occurrences of thrombophlebitis in different locations. It is also a type of condition that at least has the symptom of some phlebitis.
Protozoal dysentery is a type of dysentery characterized by a dysentery that involves protozoan infection.

Machado Joseph disease is a type of autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia and is characterized by the slow degeneration of the hindbrain. This condition has a material basis in the expansion of CAG triplet repeats (glutamine) in the ATXN3 gene. It is also known by several exact synonyms, including Azorean disease, MJD, SCA3, spinocerebellar ataxia 3, and spinocerebellar ataxia type 3. Additionally, Machado Joseph disease has an exact match with the MESH code D017827.

Capillary leak syndrome is a type of capillary disease and it is defined as a capillary disease characterized by hypotension, hypoalbuminemia, and hemoconcentration resulting from fluid and protein leakage out of capillaries into surrounding tissues. Additionally, capillary leak syndrome has an exact match with MESH:D019559.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:critical_illness_polyneuropathy rdfs:subClassOf :inflammatory_and_toxic_neuropathy .
text: critical illness polyneuropathy is a type of inflammatory and toxic neuropathy.

Autosomal dominant cerebellar ataxia is a type of autosomal dominant disease and a type of cerebellar ataxia. It is characterized by material basis in autosomal dominant inheritance. The condition, defined as a cerebellar ataxia that has material basis in autosomal dominant inheritance, is also exactly synonymous with spinocerebellar ataxia.
Labyrinthine bilateral reactive loss, a type of labyrinthine dysfunction, is also precisely known as Bilateral loss of labyrinthine reactivity and Loss of labyrinthine reactivity, bilateral.

Legg Calve Perthes disease is a type of osteochondrosis characterized by death and fracture located in the hip joint. It is also known by several exact synonyms, including Calve-Perthes' disease, Coxa plana, Juvenile osteochond-hip/pelvis, Juvenile osteochondrosis of hip and/or pelvis, Perthe's disease, Perthes disease, juvenile osteochondrosis of hip and pelvis, osteochondrosis of Legg-Calve-Perthes, and pseudocoxalgia. Additionally, it has a related synonym, Legg-Calve-Perthes symptom.

Dracunculiasis is a type of parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease, which is defined as a parasitic helminthiasis infectious disease involving parasitic infection by the larvae of the nematode Dracunculus medinensis. These larvae are transmitted to humans through drinking water containing copepods infected with the larvae. In humans, the female worm, containing larvae, burrows into the deeper connective tissues or adjacent to long bones or joints of the extremities. The worm then emerges as a whitish filament in the center of a painful ulcer, which is often accompanied by inflammation and frequently by secondary bacterial infection. Furthermore, dracunculiasis is exactly synonymous with Dracontiasis and Infection by Dracunculus medinensis.

Dipetalonemiasis is a type of filariasis, skin disease, and eye disease that involves the intersection of conditions affecting both the skin and the eye zones. It is characterized by symptoms including necrosis. Additionally, dipetalonemiasis is defined as a zoonotic infection caused by the nematode of the genus Dipetalonema, transmitted accidentally to humans from animals such as porcupines, beavers, and other mammals by mosquitoes. The adult worms of dipetalonemiasis reside subcutaneously, in body cavities, or in the eyes of humans. The death of these worms leads to hypersensitivity necrosis with eosinophils, followed by a granulomatous reaction and fibrosis. Moreover, dipetalonemiasis has exact synonyms which include Infection by Dipetalonema, Infection by Dipetalonema perstans, and dipetalonema infectious disease.

fragment:
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .

:glossopharyngeal_neuralgia rdfs:subClassOf :glossopharyngeal_nerve_disease .
text: glossopharyngeal neuralgia is a type of glossopharyngeal nerve disease.
Abnormality of glucagon secretion, which has the exact synonym "Glucagon secretion abnormality," is a type of endocrine pancreas disease.

Cerebral degeneration is a type of brain disease and is also known as brain degeneration. It is defined as a brain disease that is characterized by the loss of structure or function of neurons, including the death of neurons and loss of brain tissue. Additionally, cerebral degeneration is a condition that occurs in the cerebrum, indicating that at least one type of disease located in the cerebrum is cerebral degeneration.

Chronic tubotympanic suppurative otitis media is a type of suppurative otitis media defined as an inflammatory disease of the middle ear cleft. It is characterized by the presence of a persisting perforation within the pars tensa of the tympanic membrane, intermittent profuse muco-purulent otorrhea, and gradually progressive conductive hearing loss of more than 12 weeks duration. This condition is caused by episodes of upper respiratory infections.
Cholinergic urticaria is a type of physical urticaria, defined as a physical urticaria induced by sweating.

Sclerosing keratitis, also known exactly as Sclerokeratitis, is a type of deep keratitis that is characterized by inflammation of the anterior sclera, which leads to subsequent inflammation of the adjacent cornea with opacification of the corneal stroma. It showcases symptoms such as pain, red eyes (bloodshot eye), photophobia, tearing, and blurry vision. This condition is caused by severe anterior scleritis that triggers inflammation and injury to the adjacent corneal layer, where anterior scleritis itself can be a result of autoimmune diseases, connective tissue diseases, and infections. Additionally, sclerosing keratitis is associated with other symptoms including inflammation, pain, photophobia, corneal opacity, keratitis, and bloodshot eyes.

Chronic closed-angle glaucoma is a type of primary angle-closure glaucoma that falls under the category of diseases with the feature of ocular hypertension. It is defined as a primary angle-closure glaucoma characterized by chronic and progressive narrowing of the anterior chamber angle due to an intrinsic defect. This defect leads to blocked aqueous outflow, resulting in elevated intraocular pressure, which in turn causes optic nerve damage and visual field loss. The symptoms of chronic closed-angle glaucoma include progressive loss of peripheral vision, decreased vision, and occasionally headaches. Causes of this condition include anatomically narrow angles, defects in the trabecular meshwork, and iris abnormalities, noting that primary angle-closure glaucoma has a strong genetic component. Chronic closed-angle glaucoma is also known by its exact synonyms: anatomical narrow angle glaucoma, chronic angle-closure glaucoma, and chronic narrow angle glaucoma.

Gonadal dysgenesis is a type of disorder of sexual development and is characterized by a progressive loss of germ cells on the developing gonads of an embryo, which serves as its definition. It is also exactly synonymous with Gonadal dysgenesis syndrome.

46 XY sex reversal, also known as 46 XY gonadal dysgenesis, Pure gonadal dysgenesis 46,XY, or Swyer syndrome, is a type of gonadal dysgenesis. It is defined as a gonadal dysgenesis characterized by a normal 46,XY karyotype along with a progressive loss of germ cells on the developing gonads of an embryo.

Mixed gonadal dysgenesis is a type of gonadal dysgenesis that is defined by the progressive loss of primordial cells on the developing glands of an embryo. This condition leads to extremely hypoplastic and dysfunctional gonads, resulting in one differentiated gonad and either a streak gonad or streak testis.
